inbow-pencils-designboom-05.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/duncan-shotton-rainbow-pencils-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\n白色系列##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/duncan-shotton-rainbow-pencils-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\n黑色系列##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/duncan-shotton-rainbow-pencils-designboom-08.jpg@@\'rainbow pencils\' are currently seeking funding on kickstarter'),(125,'estudio guto requena: 由噪声转化而来的3D打印座椅','estudio guto requena 3D prints chairs in real-time with noiseall images © thiago madialardo## ## ## estudio guto requena与galeria coletivo amor de madre在2012年合作开发了这款三维数字模型座椅“nóize chairs”。设计师用手机在巴西圣保罗的街道上录音，然后将这些声音素材与原始CAD设计文件混合，一系列扭曲的座椅就这样被创造出来。\r\n其中由lina bo bardi，marcelo ferraz和marcelo suzuki设计的“giraffe chair”合成了rua santa iphigenia的声音素材，“oscar chair”\r\n则混合了来自grajaú社区的噪音，最终用3D打印的方式制作出来。## ## ## ## ##nóize chairs最初是由巴西设计师制作的3D数字模型座椅## ## ##nóize chair是通过提取美术馆环境中的噪声进行数字转化和制作的 ## ## ## ##每天, a \'metamáquina 2\' 3D打印机会提取合成文件, 制作一系列微型模型## ## ##变形## ## ##CAD 模型','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1959/estudio-guto-requena-%E7%94%B1%E5%99%AA%E5%A3%B0%E8%BD%AC%E5%8C%96%E8%80%8C%E6%9D%A5%E7%9A%843d%E6%89%93%E5%8D%B0%E5%BA%A7%E6%A4%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/noize-chairs-designboom-01.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/noize-chairs-designboom-02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/estudio-guto-requena-3D-prints-chairs-in-real-time-with-noise-designboom03.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/estudio-guto-requena-3D-prints-chairs-in-real-time-with-noise-designboom05.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/estudio-guto-requena-3D-prints-chairs-in-real-time-with-noise-designboom06.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/estudio-guto-requena-3D-prints-chairs-in-real-time-with-noise-designboom07.jpg@@'),(126,'bjarke ingels group: BIG\'s amagerforbraending ski slope incinerator',' ## ## \r\ndesignboom最近造访了bjarke ingels建筑事务所，获得了有关其最新项目“amagerforbraending ski slope incinerator”的第一手\r\n信息。该项目位于哥本哈根郊外一处密集的住宅区中，建筑屹立在首都与小镇amager之间。## ##“amagerforbraending”项目希望将工业与居住小区相结合，创造一种全新的工厂形式，建成后将成为哥本哈根的地标建筑，\r\n将工业与居住这两个完全相反的元素合为一体。这个方案重塑了发电厂概念——让普通的功能性方盒子也能提供激动人心\r\n的兴奋点——bjarke ingels团队提取工业建筑元素并将它转化成娱乐活动空间，同时，还实现了预期的商业活动。\r\n“amagerforbraending”的外墙上包裹了一层花盆表皮，不仅掩饰了原本的发电厂功能，同时还为建筑增值，创造了一个有利于\r\n环境的能源回收发电厂。为了将原本的工厂转化成吸引人的游乐目的地，BIG改造的焚化炉扩展了城市与建筑的关系，沿屋\r\n顶设计了一条滑雪道，市民可以在上面观赏哥本哈根和amager的景色，同时享受滑雪运动带来的乐趣。##这个项目最近开始动工建设，建成后将成为一座经济、环保的社会盈利性建筑。点击这里浏览designboom对\r\n“amagerforbraending”概念设计阶段的报道。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n\r\nbjarke ingels: BIG on architectural process\r\nvideo © designboom## ## ##\r\n##BIG talks about the \'amagerforbraending\' project\r\nrecording © designboom## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n2013年8月31日，world economic forum组织了一场题为“design for smart growth”的圆桌讨论会，主要探讨如何将设计与创新\r\n思想运用到竞争激烈的、可持续的经济增长中。其中bjarke ingels的项目“amagerforbraending”是本次讨论会的主要议题之一。## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1958/bjarke-ingels-group-bigs-amagerforbraending-ski-slope-incinerator.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-designboom1.jpg@@bjarke ingels group: BIG\'s amagerforbraending ski slope incinerator\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-designboom.jpg@@\r\n\'amagerforbraending\'最终模型\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-incenerator-designboom-21.jpg@@\r\n焚化炉和屋顶滑雪道\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-detail-designboom.jpg@@\r\n与绿色植被相接的屋顶斜坡\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-details.jpg@@\r\n花盆方盒子将建筑外墙包围, 同时创造了一道绿色屏障\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-studio-visit-designboom.jpg@@\r\n各种设计原型\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending.jpg@@\r\n贴在BIG事务所墙上的\'amagerforbraending\'效果图\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-sketches.jpg@@\r\nBIG事务所墙上的图板和概念效果图\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-sketches-2.jpg@@\r\n\'amagerforbraending\'渲染图展示了斯坎迪纳维亚地区景色\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-model-designboom.jpg@@ \r\n框架模型\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-interior-designboom.jpg@@\r\n会议厅渲染图\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-interiors-designboom-2.jpg@@\r\n会议厅\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-2.jpg@@\r\n行政办公区\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BIG-amagerforbraending-construction-site.jpg@@\r\n\'amagerforbraending\'施工现场\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/WEF-conference-in-copenhagen-designboom.jpg@@\r\n从左至右: bjarke ingels, 建筑师, bjarke ingels group (BIG), 丹麦; ida auken, 丹麦环境部长; david kester, 董事, thames & hudson, 英国; 王敏, 中国中央美术学院, 设计学院院长\r\nimage © designboom ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/bjarke-ingels-WEF-conference-in-copenhagen-designboom.jpg@@\r\nbjarke ingels\r\nimage © designboom##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/WEF-conference-in-copenhagen-designboom2.jpg@@\r\nworld economic forum in denmark which included paola antonelli as a discussion leader, patric frick as moderator with audience members including design author john heskett\r\nimage © designboom'),(127,'UNstudio: 日本nippon moon巨型摩天轮',' ## ## ##\r\n国际著名建筑事务所UNstudio最近受ferris wheel investment委托在日本设计一座巨大的摩天轮，这种娱乐设施在日本\r\n非常受欢迎。新摩天轮被称为“nippon moon”，它与其它同类设施有很大不同，建筑师设计了一个综合的互动系统，\r\nUNstudio与experientia合作，他们协助研究行为如何影响使用者与建筑和数字设施之间的互动关系。##游客全方位的体验在很大程度上将受到一种便携式实境增强app的影响，它主要关注三个领域：探索，乘坐和返回。乘坐\r\n摩天轮之前，游客需要在预定的时候选择好自己想要的虚拟旅程，每个单层或双层缆车都有不同的主题，包括历史、文化、\r\n或环境。在游客购票时，这种互动系统就已经开始了。数字AR平台让使用者可以随时知道在抵达之前还剩多少游览时间。\r\n在排队等候的时候，游客可以自由地在欢迎区活动，游览整个设施，不用像传统的游乐设施那样，排成一列等待进场。\r\n\r\n出发的时候，已经下载到手机或是平板电脑上的app会直观地反应各项数据信息，成为缆车之间的通信设备。这种信息\r\n设计让游客拥有独一无二的体验，增强了主题式体验的感受。不仅如此，这套设施还加入了动画和声音效果，增强了人们\r\n的感官体验。参观者自己拍摄的照片将会展示在大厅的名人堂里，成为旅途结束之后的延续。因此，这个设计希望能为游客\r\n创造一种主动式的学习氛围，同时创造美好的回忆，并对日本文化产生一定影响。虽然摩天轮的概念并不新颖，但UNstudio\r\n的设计方案将工程与设计相结合，创造了一个完整的虚拟世界。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:##业主: ferris wheel investment co.,ltd 位置: 日本面积: terminal and platform 7.200m2 building volume: terminal and platform 90.000m3 capsules: 32基地面积: 18.000m2 programme: giant observation wheel status: design##creditsUNstudio: ben van berkel, gerard loozekoot with frans van vuure, filippo lodi and harlen miller, jan kokol, wendy van der knijff, todd ebeltoft, tina kortmann, patrik noome, jeroen den hertog, iain jamieson##advisors  工程: arup tokyo + melbourne interactive design: experientia, italy动画: submarine, amsterdam可视化: mir','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1956/unstudio-%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%ACnippon-moon%E5%B7%A8%E5%9E%8B%E6%91%A9%E5%A4%A9%E8%BD%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-01.jpg@@UNstudio envision nippon moon giant observation wheel, japan\r\nall images courtesy of UNStudio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nUNstudio与arup和三菱重工合作建造这座巨型摩天轮##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\n实境增强app将nippon moon巨型摩天轮与怪兽哥斯拉相比较##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\n电子票在app上倒数计时乘坐时间##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\n摩天轮缆车##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\n渲染效果图. 每个缆车都有一个不同主题##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-07.jpg@@ 平面和剖面图##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/nippon-moon-observation-wheel-UNStudio-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\n整体剖面图显示了首层功能分布'),(128,'施少平: “莫非·卵”中国自然地貌项目回顾展',' ## ## ##施少平北京今日美术馆2013年8月25日 - 9月11日## ##中国艺术家施少平将潜心一年烧制的3,000枚实心瓷卵展示在中国最荒凉的一系列地景之中。每个瓷卵重约10公斤，3000\r\n枚卵总重逾48吨。在“莫非·卵”这件大型作品中，施少平带着这些沉甸甸的瓷卵经历了一场非凡的旅程，让它们绽放在北海\r\n冠头岭、雅丹地貌、黑戈壁、鸣沙山、甘南桑科草原等一个个望而生畏的不同地景之中。在创作团队的配合下，他仔细地放置\r\n每一枚瓷卵，让独立的个体艺术装置在每个地理位置中都能适应超大尺度的安排和展示；他还要计算时间和北海冠头岭的潮汐\r\n高度，以确保这些作品不会被自然侵蚀殆尽或被水流冲走。##\r\n最终这些历经风雨泥沙洗礼的瓷卵静卧于今日美术馆的展厅，以影像装置、摄影和文献资料全面展示施少平与他的这件大型作品\r\n“莫非·卵”所走过的一段非凡之旅。面对眼前所发生的这一场关于艺术与生命世界的演绎，相信每一位默默聆听作品并被其感动\r\n的观者都开始冥想自己内心关于生命的意义。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1957/%E6%96%BD%E5%B0%91%E5%B9%B3-%E2%80%9C%E8%8E%AB%E9%9D%9E%C2%B7%E5%8D%B5%E2%80%9D%E4%B8%AD%E5%9B%BD%E8%87%AA%E7%84%B6%E5%9C%B0%E8%B2%8C%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE%E5%9B%9E%E9%A1%BE%E5%B1%95.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-50.jpg@@\r\n黑戈壁, 甘肃省 (细节)\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013all images courtesy of today art museum##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-30.jpg@@\r\n黑戈壁, 甘肃省, 200 x 80cm (细节)\r\nphotograph, giclee, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-31.jpg@@敦煌鸣沙山, 甘肃省, 200 x 80cm\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-16.jpg@@\r\n沙丘, 敦煌, 甘肃省, （细节）\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-32.jpg@@桑科草原, 甘南, 200 x 80cm\r\nphotograph, giclee, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-18.jpg@@\r\n甘南桑科草原瓷卵装置##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-34.jpg@@ \r\n冠头岭, 北海, 广西省, 200 x 80cm\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-10.jpg@@\r\n冠头岭, 北海, 广西省（细节）\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\n雅丹地貌, 甘肃省, 200 x 80cm\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/shi-shaoping-eggs-designboom-21.jpg@@\r\n雅丹地貌, 甘肃省（细节）\r\n照片, 数码微喷, 2013'),(129,'snohetta事务所在英国的首个建筑项目: maggie\'s center',' ## ##snohetta建筑事务所分享了他们在英国设计的首个建筑项目的效果图，maggie\'s centers，这是一座癌症治疗中心。建筑拥有\r\n优雅的曲线形态，木质方盒子体量穿插在卵石形状的建筑中。为了让癌症患者能保持生存的乐趣，慈善机构“maggie\'s centers”\r\n从20世纪中期就建造了一系列康复治疗中心，希望为癌症患者提供实用的社会支持。这个令人振奋的项目来自于maggie keswick jencks，\r\n她是著名建筑理论家和景观雕塑家charles jencks的妻子。虽然maggie在1995年因乳腺癌去世，但她的遗产还留存于世，许多世界上\r\n最著名的建筑师还在继续建造这些充满希望的癌症治疗建筑。## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1955/snohetta%E4%BA%8B%E5%8A%A1%E6%89%80%E5%9C%A8%E8%8B%B1%E5%9B%BD%E7%9A%84%E9%A6%96%E4%B8%AA%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE-maggies-center.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/snohetta-first-building-in-the-UK-will-be-a-maggies-center-designboom00.jpg@@snohetta\'s first building in the UK will be a maggies center aberdeen\r\nall images courtesy of snohetta##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/snohetta-first-building-in-the-UK-will-be-a-maggies-center-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nall images courtesy of snohetta'),(130,'case design studio: 富士樱住宅',' ## ## ##\r\n为了最大限度的减少对原始基地的影响，case design studio设计的这座“富士樱住宅”是由两个相互交叉的体量组成的。穿透性的垂直柱子\r\n支撑了向外悬挑的居住空间，在组织房间布局的同时，保持了建筑与周围自然环境的关系。因此，居于中心位置的房间被设计成一个通高\r\n的大空间，刺穿整个水平建筑体量，从屋顶上穿出。为了与户外森林环境相呼应，室内隔墙采用了木板纹理。穿透建筑体量的中心柱作为\r\n餐厅使用，周围环绕着卧室、起居室、浴室、厨房、入口和榻榻米房间，各个功能空间在住宅中灵活流动。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##位置: yamanashi prefecture minamitsuru narusawa village character fuji功能: use housing (residence)业主: configuration couple基地面积: size 395m ²占地面积: 75m ²建筑面积: 67m ² (20t)\r\nfirst floor scale: ground','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1954/case-design-studio-%E5%AF%8C%E5%A3%AB%E6%A8%B1%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_001.jpg@@case design studio floats \'house in fujizakura\' on one pillarall images courtesy of case design studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_002.jpg@@(left): main approach to the house from the road\r\n(right): dining room inside the pillar##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_003.jpg@@view from balcony reveals simple yet rich finishes and layered spaces##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_004.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_005.jpg@@(left): slivers of light penetrate the interior\r\n(right): textured walls reflect the arboreal context##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_006.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_007.jpg@@pillar extends through the house as an organizing element ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_case-design-studio_house-in-fujizakura_008.jpg@@(left): kitchen\r\n(right): japanese room'),(131,'jesse kanda: 为FKA twigs新歌\'how\'s that\'设计的MV',' ## ## ##jesse kanda为FKA twigs的新歌“how\'s that”导演了一支MV。利用计算机合成图像，这位伦敦设计师延续了他对人体数字化\r\n表现的研究。设计师让变形的人体在真空空间中漂浮，用音乐引导它们移动。这些人体四肢像流体一样四处漂浮，创造了\r\n超现实和令人迷惑的视觉图像。人体之间相互缠绕，消失在短暂的音乐中。## ## ##\r\n\r\n\'FKA twigs - how\'s that\'\r\nvideo courtesy of FKA twigs## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##jesse kanda还为FKA twigs后续发行的歌曲\'water\'制作了另一支MV，虽然没有过多的实用计算机数字技术，但同样达到了\r\n超现实幻境一样的效果。## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1952/jesse-kanda-%E4%B8%BAfka-twigs%E6%96%B0%E6%AD%8Chows-that%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%9A%84mv.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jesskanda01.jpg@@jesse kanda\'s mesmerizing video for \'how\'s that\' by FKA twigsstill from jesse kanda\'s video for \'how\'s that\' by FKA twigs##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jesskanda02.jpg@@\r\nstill from jesse kanda\'s video for \'how\'s that\' by FKA twigs##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jesskanda03.jpg@@\r\nstill from jesse kanda\'s video for \'how\'s that\' by FKA twigs##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jesskanda04.jpg@@\r\nstill from jesse kanda\'s video for \'how\'s that\' by FKA twigs'),(132,'anderssen & voll为muuto设计的oslo sofa系列','oslo sofa series by anderssen & voll for muutoall images courtesy muuto## ## ##挪威设计事务所anderssen & voll为丹麦家具品牌muuto设计了“oslo”沙发系列。这组家具是在挪威西海岸制作的，包括\r\n三人沙发、椅子和椅垫——每个设计都带有内嵌式靠垫，表达了设计者对空气美学的理解。“我们希望通过一种轻质诱人\r\n的外观创造一个有机的，以人为本的沙发系列，不会在舒适度上作出妥协。”anderssen & voll解释说。“沙发坐垫上的水平\r\n分割线十分重要，它能在家具底部增加额外的舒适度”。## ## ##oslo three-seater sofa in red## ## ##oslo chair in gray## ## ##oslo pouf in red## ## ##oslo three-seater detail## ## ##oslo chair detail## ## ##oslo pouf detail','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1953/anderssen-voll%E4%B8%BAmuuto%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%9A%84oslo-sofa%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom01.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom03.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom04.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom05.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom06.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/oslo-muuto-anderssen-voll-designboom07.jpg@@'),(133,'coop himmelb(l)au: 长沙大王山旅游度假区深坑冰雪世界',' ## ##coop himmelb(l)au将设计一座120,000平方公尺深的冰窖和冰雪世界，同时配备餐厅和空中花园。这个项目是“大王山度假区”\r\n的一部分，建筑与风景如画的基地相融合，并直接建在一个水泥矿山采石坑和湖上端。建筑朝向东南，原有的采石场被故意\r\n显露出来，极具雕塑感的冰雪世界跨度为170米，悬挂在两处悬崖之间，底部是下沉的空中花园，最终创造了一个集岛屿、水、\r\n悬崖为一体的，具有全新功能的休闲空间，悬崖边的步道和坡道将建筑与自然遗产连接起来。这座独特的开放建筑建在建筑与\r\n自然景观之间，内部还设计了一个中心玻璃锥体，为底部的冰雪世界和水面提供可控制的自然光照。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## 项目信息: ## ##规划: coop himmelb(l)au wolf d. prix & partner zt gmbh主持建筑是: wolf d. prix高级项目合伙人: markus prossnigg行政协调: lei feng项目建筑师: angus schoenberger建筑设计: quirin krumbholz团队: laura ghita, crystal k.h tang, xinyu wan, paul challis, veronika janovska, sorena dumitru, philipp scherl','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1951/coop-himmelblau-%E9%95%BF%E6%B2%99%E5%A4%A7%E7%8E%8B%E5%B1%B1%E6%97%85%E6%B8%B8%E5%BA%A6%E5%81%87%E5%8C%BA%E6%B7%B1%E5%9D%91%E5%86%B0%E9%9B%AA%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/coop-himmelbau-will-design-dawang-mountain-resort-designboom00.jpg@@coop himmelb(l)au will design ice world for dawang mountain resort \r\nall images courtesy of coop himmelb(l)au##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/coop-himmelbau-will-design-dawang-mountain-resort-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nmasterplan view##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/coop-himmelbau-will-design-dawang-mountain-resort-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nvalley view'),(134,'re-write: hamura住宅','house in hamura by re-write is composed of nine triangular walls## images courtesy of re-write## ##“house in hamura”是由九个三角形的混凝土墙组成的，它们以平行方向排列，在立面上创造了一个清晰的结构组合。这座\r\n住宅是日本建筑事务所re-write设计的，水平的体量被三角形隔墙分成四个不同的住宅；它们的高差不同，差距在5.5-5.7 m\r\n之间，但还是统一在同一个建筑形体中。每套住宅都由三面墙构成（结构上是两跨）形成了紧凑狭窄的loft式居住空间，为\r\n居住者提供了灵活的平面布局，其中一跨作为车库和多功能空间使用，另外一跨是开放的两层房间和实用区域。这座自成一体\r\n的建筑突破了郊区居住区的建筑网格，创造了一个全新的，狭窄的居住空间类型。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1950/re-write-hamura%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-01.jpg@@\r\nnine concrete walls from the structural composition of the four unit dwelling##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nthe triangular shaped walls vary in height from 5.5 to 7.5m##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nthe elevation view shows deeply angled flanking walls##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\na tectonic palette of cast concrete, exposed wood and glazing##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\napertures and mezzanine spaces visually lighten the interiors ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\nlofted area enjoys an uninterrupted view ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/re-write-house-in-tamura-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\napproach'),(135,'非洲预制mamelodi pod无基础设施住宅',' ## ##\r\n约翰尼斯堡设计公司architecture for a change（AFAC）在南非设计完成了一个脱离基础设施电网的mamelodi pod预制建筑，\r\n它将成为一间足球俱乐部的队员住所。这个区域的大部分地区都没有输电网和城市基础设施，mamelodi pod方案希望能\r\n改善南非这些广泛存在的，非正式定居点的基本居住条件，根据AFAC总监dirk coester的报告，这些定居点多达2,700个。与镀锌\r\n板小屋不同，现在俱乐部成员可以住在保温隔热的空间中了，它可以容纳两张床。在运到基地组装之前，这个预制小屋被平整地\r\n包装成片。出了混凝土基础之外，建筑其它部分可以在一天之内由三人组装完成。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##[h/t] gizmodo','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1949/%E9%9D%9E%E6%B4%B2%E9%A2%84%E5%88%B6mamelodi-pod%E6%97%A0%E5%9F%BA%E7%A1%80%E8%AE%BE%E6%96%BD%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom00.jpg@@pre-fab mamelodi pod provides off-the-grid housing in africa\r\nall images courtesy of architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom01.jpg@@\r\npods are assembled off-site, flatpacked and transported to a desired location \r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nview of a connected water tank \r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nthe temporary spaces are a transitional housing solution \r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nzinc panels are insulation with a special thin material \r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom06.jpg@@\r\ninterior view \r\nimage © architecture for a change##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/mamlodi-pod-architecture-for-a-change-designboom07.jpg@@\r\npods are assembled off-site, flatpacked and transported to a desired location \r\nimage © architecture for a change'),(136,'milligram architectural studio: nestled box住宅',' ## ## 当地建筑事务所milligram architectural studio在东京cho-fu设计了一座住宅建筑“nestled box”。建筑外立面最先完成，选用了\r\n纹理方向不同的木板，最终形成了编织一样的效果。常规的建筑立面上叠加了上百个有节奏排列的窗户，这些大小比例不同\r\n的窗洞让室内全天充满自然光照。在建造过程中，整个空间完全封闭，直到室内框架搭接完毕并覆盖上一层木板材料之后。\r\n这个独特的设计搭配了大量绿色植物，它们充满整座住宅，有的靠在窗台上，有的悬挂在屋顶。住宅围绕一个独立的户外走廊\r\n布置，它延续到室内，在垂直方向上向中庭空间开放。中心楼梯延续了编织图案的主题风格，连接了错列的上层楼板，这里是\r\n公共的起居空间，在空间和视觉上相互开放。住宅房间被设计成loft一样的形式，通高的墙面只围合了最私密的功能空间。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n##netsled box from milligram studio on vimeo.','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1948/milligram-architectural-studio-nestled-box%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_001.jpg@@milligram architectural studio designs house as \'nestled box\'\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_002.jpg@@\r\nweather wears well on the facade\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_003.jpg@@\r\n(left):the checkerboard facade pattern enlarge the dwelling\'s appearance\r\n(right): a long corridor circles the nestled box\r\nimages © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_004.jpg@@\r\ngarage and main entrance of nestled box\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_005.jpg@@\r\n(left):lush plants fill the home\r\n(right): curtains make for flexible rooms at the entry\r\nimages © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_006.jpg@@\r\nthe basement\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_007.jpg@@\r\nconstructed completely of wood, the house has a warm glow\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_008.jpg@@\r\nfurnished and filled with plants, the upper floor is ready for family life\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_009.jpg@@\r\nhundreds of windows wash the house with light\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_010.jpg@@\r\nbefore plants and tapestries hang from horizontal surfaces, the large atrium visually connects every room\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_011.jpg@@\r\nplants and tapestries decorate the vertical void\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_012.jpg@@\r\n(left): urban green space\r\n(right): leaves dangle above like a chandelier\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_nestled-box_013.jpg@@\r\nplants with practical functions\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio'),(137,'BIG: 入围丹麦最大医院建筑设计竞赛',' ## ## BIG architects与其它两家事务所入围了丹麦最大医院的建筑设计竞赛。arup，WHR和BIG设计的分层绿色屋顶方案最终入围\r\n竞赛第二阶段，这个竞赛将设计全新的north zealand医院，或称nyt hospital nordsjælland，建成后将成为丹麦最大的医院建筑，\r\n面积达124,000平方米。基地面积为30公顷，位于哥本哈根北部，是一片郁郁葱葱的原始林地。这个大型医院项目将成为这一地区\r\n新城规划的补充部分，同时兴建的还有一座车站。其中有一个需要“outof-the-box”的功能空间，内部囊括了理性的、流线型物流功能，\r\n出入口和一体化综合空间，这座医院将成为周边社区的主要辅助设施，同时提供最高质量的医疗护理。BIG设计的这个低层建筑包含\r\n一系列浅水池，同时巧妙地避让了远处的fredericksborg castle，没有形成视线遮挡。室内空间也被释放开来，一些特殊的设计要求，\r\n包括空气质量和声音缓冲对病患治疗都是非常重要的因素。总而言之，这个方案还进一步考虑了医院未来的发展需求，即“为不确定\r\n性因素和变化做准备”。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##  ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1947/big-%E5%85%A5%E5%9B%B4%E4%B8%B9%E9%BA%A6%E6%9C%80%E5%A4%A7%E5%8C%BB%E9%99%A2%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%AB%9E%E8%B5%9B.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom00.jpg@@BIG and arup among shortlisted to design denmark\'s largest hospital \r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-10.jpg@@\r\nthe design respects the pond and other features of the untouched landscape\r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-11.jpg@@\r\nentrance to the hospital\r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-12.jpg@@\r\ninside a hospital courtyard\r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-13.jpg@@\r\nthe undulating green roof reflects the nature of the site\r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-14.jpg@@\r\nsports fields are interspersed in the courtyards to promote recovery, rehabilitation and relaxation\r\nimage © BIG architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BIG-shortlisted-to-design-denmarks-biggest-hospital-designboom-15.jpg@@\r\ninside the operating room\r\nimage © BIG architects'),(138,'iida archiship studio: 轻井泽omizubata N house','all images courtesy of iida archiship studio ## ## 由iida archiship studio设计的“omni zubata N house”位于日本轻井泽，建筑师利用夸张的坡屋顶形式创造了一个终极全景露台。这座度假别墅的起居室部分从混凝土外沿向内退让，外墙覆盖了一层木板材料。不对称的竖框玻璃窗沿着屋顶边界线布置，让\r\n居住者可以从二层书房观赏到周围的森林景色。室内木板墙面的边界线沿着水平窗框布置。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##基地面积:832.35㎡占地面积:157.70㎡结构 & 层数: ｗ+s／1basement & 2stories','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1946/iida-archiship-studio-%E8%BD%BB%E4%BA%95%E6%B3%BDomizubata-n-house.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_001.jpg@@omizubata N house by iida archiship studio reframes the gable##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_002.jpg@@\r\nview of the corridor and built volume wrapped in a concrete shell##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_003.jpg@@\r\ninteriors are a composition of warm wood cladding##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_004.jpg@@\r\nboardmarked bands of concrete characterize and open-air hallway##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_005.jpg@@\r\nthe recessed main volume follows the lines of a simple gable and creates the ultimate terrace##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_iida-archiship-studio_Omizubata-N-house_006.jpg@@\r\n(left):a lofted study area overlooks the thick surrounding forest\r\n(right): night view of the tranquil summer home'),(139,'cory stevens:万花筒建筑摄影','kaleidoscopic architectural compositions by cory stevensimage courtesy and © cory stevens## ## ## ##加拿大摄影师cory stevens将抽象化的建筑物融入到他最新的系列作品“deconstructed. reimagined.”中。摄影师捕捉了\r\n建筑物、天花板、墙面和窗户，重新排列组合它们的位置，将原有形态转化成万花筒一样的效果。不规则的分形图案设计来自于\r\n螺旋式的圆塔，将建筑立面和分段式摩天楼的投影相互重叠，创造出光学上的对称性图案。stevens选取了当代和历史建筑，作为\r\n一种视觉影响，展现了摄影师对那些日常所见的塔楼、纪念碑和住所的最初视角。这一系列复杂的作品将融合了摄影、建筑和数字设计。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1945/cory-stevens%E4%B8%87%E8%8A%B1%E7%AD%92%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91%E6%91%84%E5%BD%B1.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-10.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-11.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cory-stevens-architectural-photography-designboom-12.jpg@@\r\nimage © cory stevens'),(140,'echoviren pavilion: 世界第一座3D打印建筑',' ## ##smith | allen是来自美国加州奥克兰的设计工作室，它们设计了第一座全3D打印的建筑体。建筑位于光影斑驳的红树林中，\r\n这个设计与基地环境紧密相连，模仿了绿色植物的木质部和韧皮部，并将这些元素抽象化。这个设计是project 387的一部分，\r\n它本身是一个集艺术家、设计师和制造者为一体的实验性跨学科项目，由585个联锁组件构成，共花费10,800个小时进行3D打印。这座10x10x8英尺的建筑物需要四天时间组装，并开始与森林建立起标志性的关联——建筑是用以植物为基础的生物塑料制作的，\r\n可以在森林中分解，创造无数个微型栖息地，编织形态的墙面最终会和生态系统融为一体。## ## ##\r\n\r\nthe video details the fabrication and assembly process \r\nvideo © TERRA TOXIS## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1944/echoviren-pavilion-%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%80%E5%BA%A73d%E6%89%93%E5%8D%B0%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom00.jpg@@echoviren pavilion: the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom09.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom10.jpg@@\r\nechoviren pavilion reportedly the world\'s first 3D printed architecture \r\nimage © smith | allen studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/echoviren-worlds-first-3D-printed-architecture-smith-allen-studio-designboom11.jpg@@\r\nprototype view \r\nimage © smith | allen studio'),(141,'milligram architectural studio: 轻井泽度假别墅soaring villa on the wing',' ## ##由milligram建筑事务所设计的“villa on the wing”位于东京轻井泽地区一处倾斜的林地中，轻井泽从19世纪末期就成为\r\n东京市民最喜欢的夏日度假胜地。这座度假别墅由两个断裂的体量构成，底部是曲线形的楼板，多层玻璃窗和带模板\r\n纹路的混凝土墙交替着显示或隐藏了室内的功能空间。从远处看，这座建筑仿佛悬浮在空中，同时躲避了森林中现有\r\n的树木，大屋顶上的开口让树木巧妙地穿透建筑空间。谨慎排列的混凝土底柱在视觉上与戏剧化的三角形屋顶形成对比。## ## ## ## ## ##image © milligram architectural studio## ## ##image © milligram architectural studio## ## ##image © milligram architectural studio## ## ##项目信息: ## ##功能: 别墅位置: karuizawa层数: 1f结构: hybrid','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1943/milligram-architectural-studio-%E8%BD%BB%E4%BA%95%E6%B3%BD%E5%BA%A6%E5%81%87%E5%88%AB%E5%A2%85soaring-villa-on-the-wing.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_villa-on-the-wing-1_001.jpg@@villa on the wing soars over hills by milligram architectural studio\r\nimage © villa on the wing by milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_villa-on-the-wing-1_002.jpg@@\r\nnight viewof the eaves on soaring villa on the wing by milligram architectural studio\r\nimage © milligram architectural studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_villa-on-the-wing-1_003.jpg@@\r\nangled eaves provide covered spaces for the entrance##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_villa-on-the-wing-1_004.jpg@@\r\nbands of glazing and board-marked concrete provide tectonic dynamism##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_milligram_villa-on-the-wing-1_005.jpg@@\r\nthe holiday house is composed of two concrete volumes'),(142,'inside 2013 设计竞赛获胜作品',' ## ##inside 2013 competition设计竞赛向学生和各个设计领域的年轻创造者发出邀请——可以是建筑师、室内设计师、家具设计师、\r\n数码制作、平面设计师、灯光设计师、产品设计师。围绕即将到老的新技术作为潜在主题，竞赛方提出了诸如此类的问题：\r\n今天，我们用什么样的愿望来评价设计？；在一个急速增长的网络文化中，什么东西可以让我们的设计斩断那些虚拟噪声，\r\n开始一个新对话？；不断进化的媒体形式是如何影响我们的日常通讯的？竞赛方要求参赛者能表现出科技对当今世界带来的\r\n影响，以及它在一些增殖领域里的影响，例如装置文化和社交网络，以及科技在生产过程中的作用，它是如何帮助我们评价\r\n和组织工作方式的。将这些信息组合成一种可以促进当代青年人研究、探索和创新的方式，不仅仅是简单地从已有科技成果\r\n出发，而是思考为什么能把这些人当作当代的设计师，最终收集上来的参赛作品涵盖了以下几个概念——从社会到建筑——\r\n展示了那些创造性地解决了数字与消费文化间年龄差距问题的新想法，以及它将如何在建造领域发挥更大作用。## ##竞赛由morpholio project组织举办，今年INSIDE competition的获奖者如下： ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##future voices winner, jury winner## ## ##future voices winner, eyetime winner (based on crowd sourced data)## ## ##future voices winner, jury honor awards## ## ##future voices winner, jury honor awards## ## ##future voices winner, jury honor awards## ## ##future voices winner, jury honor awards## ## ## ## ## ## ##morpholio special recognition','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1942/inside-2013-%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%AB%9E%E8%B5%9B%E8%8E%B7%E8%83%9C%E4%BD%9C%E5%93%81.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-01.jpg@@inside 2013 competition winners announced\r\n\'hive city / elevator B: an urban bee habitat\' \r\nemerging talent winner, jury winner##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nkitchen of elements by seda zirek\r\nemerging talent winner, eyetime winner (based on crowd sourced data)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nshibuya tower by john szot\r\nemerging talent winner, jury honor awards##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nSPLASH! mosaic designs by paul reiss\r\nemerging talent winner, jury honor awards##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\ninside a sinkhole: a convent by javier galindo\r\nemerging talent winner, jury honor award##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nseed library + ascending urban garden by danielle krug\r\nemerging talent winner, jury honor awards##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\nwhite concrete and wood stool by franck divay\r\nemerging talent winner, jury honor awards##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\ntango pouf by ryszard manczak\r\nemerging talent winners, jury honor awards##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-11.jpg@@\r\ngoat island, sydney by brad mitchell##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-12.jpg@@\r\nempyrean lighting: LED lamp by kelly cones##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-13.jpg@@\r\nrestaurant by thaddeus lee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-14.jpg@@\r\nicarus by jason khoo##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-15.jpg@@\r\nwall shelf by rubin gurung##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-16.jpg@@\r\nroom in the river by veronica acosta##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-17.jpg@@\r\n\'the portland hostel\' by david cho\r\nfuture voices winner, jury honor award##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-09.jpg@@\r\nfilament mind by brian brush\r\nmorpholio special recognition##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/inside-comptition-2013-winners-designboom-10.jpg@@\r\nsusi-teria by richard sarrach with photo by amy barkow'),(143,'LAb[au]: m0za1que永久性动态光艺术装置',' ## ## \r\n“m0za1que”是一个永久性动态光艺术装置，它被安装在法国annecy-le-vieux，maison mecatronique入口大厅的主体墙面上。\r\n这件作品是比利时机构LAb[au]创作的，它通过光学现象将动态与色彩相结合。3.4m x 6m的墙面被分成26x15的方块，总计\r\n390块，它们被一个10cm范围的线型驱动器驱动。独立的动态控制系统创造了三维的几何图案，遵循了细胞自动装置的设计\r\n逻辑。白天，程序化的图案回产生黑色的阴影，到了夜晚就出现彩色的阴影。红、绿、蓝三台投影仪在墙上创造了一个统一\r\n的白色灯光效果——方块下的阴影也从黑白变成彩色。彩色发光表面会根据立面的运动出现或小时。##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1940/labau-m0za1que%E6%B0%B8%E4%B9%85%E6%80%A7%E5%8A%A8%E6%80%81%E5%85%89%E8%89%BA%E6%9C%AF%E8%A3%85%E7%BD%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LAbau-m0za1que-designboom01.jpg@@LAb[au]\'s m0za1que a kinetic light art installation\r\nall images courtesy of LAb[au]##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_3_1376905188_e68c66001af738ef80ec451c0639601a.JPG@@\r\nm0za1que relates motion with color through the phenomena of light##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/LAbau-m0za1que-designboom02.jpg@@\r\n the 3.4m x 6m wall is divided into 26x15 squares, each of the 390 tiles is motorized by a linear actuator##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_6_1376905188_29b27e1d8609d06caeda90aac2d8270a.JPG@@\r\nduring the day the programmed motifs draw black shadows and in the evening colored shadows appear##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_8_1376905188_a1fccb800372aaa8d47cebe59c9e5202.JPG@@\r\nthree light-projectors in primary colors of red, green, and blue creates a uniform white illumination on the wall##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_9_1376905188_09fc5cdfe4002d1f6d3158be70c38562.JPG@@\r\nlooking down onto the illuminated moving facade##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_10_1376905188_51cfd84f0deaac43d52440eed1314596.JPG@@\r\n the colored illuminated surfaces appear and disappear according to the facade\'s movement##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_11_1376905188_c02341d62d2d999f7be8cef2562fa4d6.JPG@@\r\nthe individually controlled motion system creates three-dimensional reliefs of geometric patterns##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_1_1376905188_983a6722cb731f1997954782ce8527de.JPG@@\r\nm0za1que 15x26 is installed at the maison mecatronique, annecy-le-vieux, france##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_2_1376905188_c9deeb627ec5e297f0c5a5e553426ccd.JPG@@\r\nthe wall without any illuminated light##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/377062/2013-08-19/img_12_1376905188_389c1455b4143d189117e97824223e3c.JPG@@\r\ndetail of the m0za1que motors'),(144,'a mirror darkly: 镜面陶瓷碗',' ## ## ##苏格兰裔斯德哥尔默设计师nick ross设计的“a mirror darkly”用现代的方法重新诠释了陶瓷碗不为人知的历史，通过这个设计\r\n他想要探究，臆测和可能的误解是如何改变我们对过去的看法的。有些历史学家相信，石器时代晚期，虽然还没有混凝土\r\n存在的证据，但一些可能盛了水的小型陶瓷碗其实是一种放在桌面上的镜子。由于缺乏证据，这一理论只是增加了出土器物\r\n的神秘性。“a mirror darkly”是这种陶瓷碗镜子的当代诠释，有人可能会问：这到底是一个新设计，还是只是一个改造？当\r\n这句话从人们口中说出的瞬间，它们已经变成事实——不管这一理论有多虚假。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1941/a-mirror-darkly-%E9%95%9C%E9%9D%A2%E9%99%B6%E7%93%B7%E7%A2%97.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_1_1376404938_0eeec1c6ee56092b3829214076ec9a33.jpg@@a mirror darkly questions historic usage of the ceramic bowl\r\nall images courtesy of nick ross##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_2_1376404938_95c43e67aceb5457cf9e2956d31ec722.jpg@@\r\nface on view##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_3_1376404938_48dd2399e0c60e6a9bb87b6b18bb07f6.jpg@@\r\nas wall mounted mirror##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_4_1376404938_c795cd0981f4a99121f517435500d839.jpg@@\r\n the print sits between the two sheets of glass##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_5_1376404938_e81787cccc7c37ed2a8d3286d65dd004.jpg@@\r\nthe body of the mirror is made from spun copper which is oxidized and then waxed##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_6_1376404938_38bb48b1df001f7d9a9764f5e1dd99fb.jpg@@\r\nclose up of gradient print##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_7_1376404938_8d492ee1b1a5d72e6468fd0914f4a701.jpg@@\r\nearly sketches##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_8_1376404938_2893fec2b91a3c01c4dc5c6f93ed0809.jpg@@\r\nspinning the copper body##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_9_1376404938_0bbfede879764152da9e4293bd2247fc.jpg@@\r\napplying the silver oxide before waxing the surface##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/324737/2013-08-13/img_10_1376404938_32566ecb2f2032be8e3099c1557aa13e.jpg@@\r\nearly prototype'),(145,'jair straschnow\'s proeflokaal: butcher\'s tears品酒室桌椅设计',' ## ## ##阿姆斯特丹设计师jair straschnow设计了一套适应性极强的桌/椅，可以配合多种灵活的空间配置，这个设计是新proeflokaal\r\n——butcher\'s tears品酒室的一部分。这座小啤酒厂位于阿姆斯特丹，专门酿造精致且未经过滤的鲜啤酒。这组桌/椅是用废钢管\r\n和竹子材料制作的，灵活的构造提供了无数种使用可能：从一张长桌到可以容纳50个品酒人的凳子。工业化的摇臂壁灯从墙面\r\n上伸展出来——它们可以灵活调节，根据不同的桌椅配置旋转方向，创造不同类型的灯光和空间效果。## ##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1938/jair-straschnows-proeflokaal-butchers-tears%E5%93%81%E9%85%92%E5%AE%A4%E6%A1%8C%E6%A4%85%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jair-straschnow-butchers-tears-designboom001.jpg@@jair straschnow\'s proeflokaal: tasting room at butcher\'s tears\r\nall images courtesy of jair straschnow##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jair-straschnow-butchers-tears-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nbutcher\'s tears table/bench has numerous seating options and is divided with a large bar at the back##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jair-straschnow-butchers-tears-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nthe furniture can be arranged to form one long table to a maximum seated capacity of 50 thirsty beer drinkers##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jair-straschnow-butchers-tears-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nproeflokaak\'s furniture stacked clearing the interior space##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_7_1376947332_8f14e45fceea167a5a36dedd4bea2543.jpg@@\r\noptional park-like chair seats##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_1_1376947332_c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b.jpg@@\r\nthe table/bench is made from rejected steel pipes and bamboo##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_2_1376947332_c81e728d9d4c2f636f067f89cc14862c.jpg@@\r\nthe butcher\'s table collapsed##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_10_1376947332_d3d9446802a44259755d38e6d163e820.jpg@@\r\nlong table setting##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_8_1376947332_c9f0f895fb98ab9159f51fd0297e236d.jpg@@\r\nswivel arm lamps##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_9_1376947332_45c48cce2e2d7fbdea1afc51c7c6ad26.jpg@@\r\nsix beers are offered on tap##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/316279/2013-08-19/img_11_1376947332_6512bd43d9caa6e02c990b0a82652dca.jpg@@\r\nthe space being used by thirsty customers'),(146,'EM2N: 瑞士电影资料馆',' ## ## ##EM2N设计的瑞士实验电影院swiss cinematheque已经进入到第二阶段。原有的老建筑由几个成线型关系的体量组成，扩建方案\r\n将增建几座新楼，同时将老建筑形式转化成一个综合的，由不同高度的平行体量组成的相互冲突的形式。建筑看起来仍旧呈线型\r\n排列，只在两端露出尖角。这种层次也延续到室内空间中。三个交通系统在垂直方向上穿透了平行的墙面，让使用者可以直接体验\r\n连续的组织空间。然而，公共区域都集中在penthaz i，而资料馆本身在penthaz ii街道的远端，是一个全底下的储藏空间，为宝贵的文化\r\n作品提供最优保护。建筑立面采用锈蚀钢板材料，将新老建筑联系到了一起。##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1939/