boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo01.jpg@@\'the urban crossing城市过道\' by aedas, shanghai, china\r\nall images courtesy of aedas##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo02.jpg@@从河中浮出的大台阶##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo03.jpg@@建筑和广场鸟瞰图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo04.jpg@@主入口##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo05.jpg@@庭院##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo06.jpg@@屋顶平台##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo08.jpg@@空中休息厅##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo07.jpg@@空中休息厅##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo09.jpg@@鸟瞰图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo10.jpg@@临空经济园区鸟瞰图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo11.jpg@@总平面图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo13.jpg@@剖面图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo12.jpg@@总平面图##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo14.jpg@@概念生成##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo15.jpg@@交通流线设计##/weblog/images/images_2/lauren/aedas/uo16.jpg@@内部功能分析'),(195,'matteo thun: fire house',' ## ## ##\r\n意大利建筑师matteo thun为德国公司ecolohe设计的这座8m的方形建筑物“fire house”利用当地材料，由当地居民建造完成。\r\n建筑立面覆盖了一层松木瓦，这种树木在当地十分常见。建筑形式，尤其是屋顶，参考了意大利alto adige地区的san vito教堂。\r\n这座建筑达到了碳中和，并且零废弃物。它容纳了500 -kW的锅炉燃料。排气口上的滤网减少了因为燃烧而产生的颗粒物污染。\r\n这个项目也是面积达175英亩的bad aibling前美军基地改造计划中的一部分，周围有超过700户居民。“fire house”通过额外的\r\n加热锅炉为这一地区提供冬季供暖，夏天则转换成太阳能发电厂。有几所研究生物质能和电力系统管理与优化的大学正监控着\r\n这个计划。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##(left): san vito in the italian region of alto adige. photo courtesy b&o gruppe\r\n(right): completed biomasseheizhaus in bad aibling. photo © walter wehner## ##项目信息: ## ##建筑师: matteo thun项目团队: b & o saatinvest heizhaus (manufacturer); hdg bavaria (woodchip boiler); ecolohe (flokets chips producer); schrader (particulate filter)业主: b & o housing, bad aibling位置: bad aiblingen, district mietrachingen, access via ebersbergerstraße完工: 2011credit: b & o housing, bad aibling','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1935/matteo-thun-fire-house.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-01.jpg@@matteo thun designs \'fire house\' with carbon neutral footprint\r\nphoto © walter wehner\r\nall images courtesy of matteo thun and b & o gruppe##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nentry door shows the scale of this 8m cube\r\nphoto © walter wehner##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\n(left) detail of larch shingle siding \r\n(right): the metal chimney and front facade contrast against wooden cladding\r\nphotos © walter wehner\r\n ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nroof detail\r\nphoto © walter wehner\r\n ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\nthe heating plant was built with local labor and construction materials\r\nphoto © walter wehner##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/matteo-thun-fire-house-designboom-10.jpg@@'),(196,'shinobu koizumi小泉忍: 不会化的雪人家具',' ## ## ##为了能留住雪花的美丽瞬间并在整个冬天享受玩雪的乐趣，日本设计师shinobu koizumi小泉忍设计了这个“winter memories”\r\n系列。这些设计看上去是用雪做的日常用品，实际上是用盐晶体和环氧树脂制作的。设计师制作了一个可以储物的凳子和\r\n一个雪人花瓶，这种仿雪材料像纸张一样轻，而且质地松软，即使冬天已经过去，人们还是可以享受玩雪的乐趣。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1934/shinobu-koizumi%E5%B0%8F%E6%B3%89%E5%BF%8D-%E4%B8%8D%E4%BC%9A%E5%8C%96%E7%9A%84%E9%9B%AA%E4%BA%BA%E5%AE%B6%E5%85%B7.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_1_1376869527_64eaaf86cd406ebf2f09081eec004e7e.jpg@@shinobu koizumi\'s useful snow-like objects won\'t melt away\r\nall images courtesy of shinobu koizumi##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shinobu-koizumi-winter-memories-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe snowman vase is constructed from salt crystals fixed with epoxy resin##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_6_1376869527_224604a1169e6ff74edd022f4817516b.jpg@@\r\nthe object can hold a flower or pen, which look like arms and detachable test tubes makes it easy to renew the water##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_7_1376869527_8466f5504ad2ad46b84ada6d8e10c4a8.jpg@@\r\nsurface of the desktop snowman with its snow-like appearance##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_3_1376869527_35a7e1b8d3143ed98b0fd41978a54b1a.jpg@@\r\nthe snowball paper-weight is also made from salts fixed by epoxy resin and has a metal weight built in##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shinobu-koizumi-winter-memories-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nsnowball weight##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_4_1376869527_c72386b357f29751502d6b3ed89b10ce.jpg@@\r\nthe snowball can be used as a paperweight, it won\'t melt away and it\'s not wet##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shinobu-koizumi-winter-memories-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nsnow covered table##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_9_1376869527_28e15519ef28f85b0ccc7ff93f37bc95.jpg@@\r\nthe snow on the table acts as a cover for storage##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_10_1376869527_cd7d7cd219fd534298091245b4d51fd6.jpg@@\r\ninside of the cover showing the space to contain objects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/327253/2013-08-18/img_11_1376869527_351ffe06c315df7ab1dcb6bee6ff11c2.jpg@@\r\nsurface of the thick snow made of salts fixed by epoxy resin##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shinobu-koizumi-winter-memories-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nan experiment for the project, a mitten sprinkled with sugar'),(197,'anish kapoor: jupiter artland“suck”铁笼漩涡装置',' ## ## ##由著名艺术家anish kapoor创作的装置“suck”位于英国爱丁堡的jupiter artland，这座17英尺高的方形铁笼内部有一个深不见底\r\n的漩涡，它与宁静的树林环境并置，让人产生一种恐惧不舒服的感觉。anish kapoor捕捉了一种可怕的诱惑力，让平静的自然环境\r\n看起来有一种黑暗恐怖的感觉。参观者只能在沉重的铁栅栏外窥见中心处那个无底的漩涡，这个无尽的深渊让人产生痛苦焦灼\r\n的不安感，生怕被推下去。“suck”延续了kapoor作品的一贯特性，他用抽象的结构体或雕塑扭曲人们对空间的感知。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1933/anish-kapoor-jupiter-artland%E2%80%9Csuck%E2%80%9D%E9%93%81%E7%AC%BC%E6%BC%A9%E6%B6%A1%E8%A3%85%E7%BD%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jupiter-artland-anish-kapoor-suck-designboom-07.jpg@@anish kapoor\'s suck at jupiter artland is a caged vortex \r\nall images courtesy of jupiter artland##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jupiter-artland-anish-kapoor-suck-designboom-08.jpg@@ \r\na detail of the bottomless vortex##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jupiter-artland-anish-kapoor-suck-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nthe caged structure in the middle of the space##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jupiter-artland-anish-kapoor-suck-designboom-10.jpg@@\r\na jarring site for the forestscape##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jupiter-artland-anish-kapoor-suck-designboom-09.jpg@@\r\n\'suck\' during a snowstorm'),(198,'安藤忠雄: 济州凤凰度假村genius loci和glass house','all images courtesy of xin li## ## ##日本著名建筑师安藤忠雄从phoenix island的美丽景色中得到灵感，设计了这两座“genius loci”和“glass house”，建筑师希望在美丽的\r\n景观中创造一个安宁的冥想空间。genius loci是以岛屿的守护神来命名的，这座一流的冥想建筑位于seopjikoji（涉地岬）。建筑\r\n两侧是人工水瀑，而sungsan山的顶峰就坐落在建筑不远处。主要的走廊设有一个开放屋顶，让内部空间暴露在岛屿天空下。另一\r\n座建筑glass house是一个简单的混凝土框架体量，其简洁的构思源于平面几何学，一楼有通往蓝色画廊和阳光自助餐厅的宿舍，\r\n二楼有高级综合餐厅‘Mint’餐厅，可以观赏到附近济州岛的美景。玻璃屋内有称作‘四季园’的野外庭园，通过此庭园您可以步入\r\n远古的大自然。这一组建筑与景观相融合，而不是将景观包围住，建筑师在构造上的思考和设计创造了一个内向型的冥想空间。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1932/%E5%AE%89%E8%97%A4%E5%BF%A0%E9%9B%84-%E6%B5%8E%E5%B7%9E%E5%87%A4%E5%87%B0%E5%BA%A6%E5%81%87%E6%9D%91genius-loci%E5%92%8Cglass-house.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom00-.jpg@@tadao ando designs genius loci for phoenix island##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom01.jpg@@\r\ngenius loci draws from the architecture of the land##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe building and the landscape are synthesized in the network of building##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom03.jpg@@\r\ncirculation is aimed at meditative movement##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nglass house employs a concrete frame and ample glazed to optimize island views##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom05.jpg@@\r\ncharacteristically cast concrete##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tadao-ando-genius-loci-phoenix-island-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nview of the material palette'),(199,'tham & videgard: 混凝土坡屋顶夏日住宅',' ##斯德哥尔摩建筑事务所tham and videgard与我们分享了他们最新设计的summerhouse lågno项目。这座建筑采用现浇混凝土\r\n做法，建筑形式类似于船坞，最大特点是横向的坡屋顶设计。褶皱一般的屋顶创造了一系列层高不同的室内空间，同时还\r\n提供了一个完全开放的起居空间。虽然房间进深很浅，但连续的玻璃门将水畔景色全部引入到白色的室内空间中。滑动玻璃\r\n门将大海与天空的美景引入到较小的北向房间。这个方案在材料选择上受到了当地文脉的启发，建筑的重量感和颜色都与\r\n环绕基地的群岛花岗岩基岩相互联系。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑师: tham & videgård arkitekter团队: bolle tham and martin videgård (chief architects)\r\nanna jacobson (project architect)室内设计: tham & videgård arkitekter景观设计: tham & videgård arkitekter结构工程: sweco, mathias karlsson位置: undisclosed业主: private占地面积: 140 m2方案日期: 2010完工: 2012## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1931/tham-videgard-%E6%B7%B7%E5%87%9D%E5%9C%9F%E5%9D%A1%E5%B1%8B%E9%A1%B6%E5%A4%8F%E6%97%A5%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom00.jpg@@concrete gables make up summerhouse lagno by tham & videgard\r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nthe main volume connects to a smaller space that houses the sauna \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nsliding doors open the living space to the bay \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom03.jpg@@\r\ninteriors are light filled \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nkitchen and dining spaces are smartly composed within the gabled form \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nthe in situ cast concrete is met with warm ash cladding \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom06.jpg@@\r\ntham & videgard unveil summerhouse lagno\r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nthe home articulates a clear line on the site \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nthe home enjoys waterfront views \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/tham-and-videgard-summer-house-lagno-designboom09.jpg@@\r\nboard-marked concrete adds a tectonic richness to the facade \r\nimages © Åke E:son lindman'),(200,'安装在宜家玻璃杯上的3D打印配件',' ## ## ##\r\n来自法国AD-3D工作室的保加利亚设计师和艺术家aleksandar dimitrov为常见的宜家pokal玻璃杯设计了一个小配件，\r\n“clip on glass”。这个3D打印设计将通常用于喝水的容器转化成一个小花瓶。设计师用最少的材料，打印了规格为\r\n9/9/6 cm的小配件。 制作材料选用聚酰胺纤维——这是一种强韧灵活的材料，安装过程中，它可以轻易地拉伸或缩小，\r\n以适应玻璃杯口。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1930/%E5%AE%89%E8%A3%85%E5%9C%A8%E5%AE%9C%E5%AE%B6%E7%8E%BB%E7%92%83%E6%9D%AF%E4%B8%8A%E7%9A%843d%E6%89%93%E5%8D%B0%E9%85%8D%E4%BB%B6.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/AD-3D-click-on-vase-designboom00.jpg@@3D printed clip on vase modifies drinking glass\r\nall images courtesy of AD-3D##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/AD-3D-click-on-vase-designboom01.jpg@@\r\na simple click connects the piece to an ordinary glass##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/AD-3D-click-on-vase-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nclip on vase using ikea pokal glass##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/AD-3D-click-on-vase-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nthe 3D printed accessory transforms the drinking glass into a vase, suitable for holding flowers'),(201,'henning larsen赢得斯图加特国会媒体中心设计竞赛',' ## henning larsen architects建筑事务所最近赢得了斯图加特城堡公园新市民和媒体中心的建筑设计竞赛，这一方案将\r\n丰富整个地区的公共空间。下沉式的露天剧场位于绿地中，面朝现代主义风格的baden-württburg国会大楼。底层架空的玻璃立面\r\n大楼是二战后首座国会建筑，是民主进程的象征。因为这座公园是非常有名的景点，这座议会大楼每年都会吸引超过65,000人次\r\n的参观者，下沉式的市民和媒体中心让议会大厦成为一个畅通无阻的地标建筑物。建筑形式明确大胆，中心有一个挖空的大空间，\r\n建筑师希望将它设计成一个小型的城市广场，与已有的国会大楼在功能上相呼应。圆形的玻璃立面将周围的绿色景观引入室内，下沉\r\n的多功能空间则作为举办政治会议或公共文化活动的场所。连接大厅、会议中心和展览区可以从主要的国会大楼中隔离、关闭，保证安全。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ##项目信息:  ## ##业主: land baden-württemberg, stuttgart团队: henning larsen architects, knippers helbig建筑面积: 2,800 m2竞赛: 竞赛一等奖henning larsen architects设计团队: louis becker (partner), werner frosch (project director) daniel baumann, \r\nsonny holmberg, juliane demel, luísa paiva, eileen dorer.## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1929/henning-larsen%E8%B5%A2%E5%BE%97%E6%96%AF%E5%9B%BE%E5%8A%A0%E7%89%B9%E5%9B%BD%E4%BC%9A%E5%AA%92%E4%BD%93%E4%B8%AD%E5%BF%83%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%AB%9E%E8%B5%9B.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/henning-larsen-win-citizen-and-media-center-stuttgart-designboom00.jpg@@henning larsen will design parliament media center in stuttgart \r\nimage © henning larsen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/henning-larsen-win-citizen-and-media-center-stuttgart-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nthe inner city park will be further enriched by the sunken interactive center \r\nimage © henning larsen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/henning-larsen-win-citizen-and-media-center-stuttgart-designboom02.jpg@@\r\ncylindrical glazing creates a daylight-filled interior\r\nimage © henning larsen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/henning-larsen-win-citizen-and-media-center-stuttgart-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nthe media center will behave like a greened agora \r\nimage © henning larsen'),(202,'sabrina fossi: freakish极简挂钟',' ## ##\r\n为了将时间的概念极简化，意大利工业设计师sabrina fossi设计了这一系列大胆而简洁的“freakishclock” 。这个手工制作的设计直径30 cm，厚度2 cm，拥有清晰锐利的表现方式——钟表上分钟的变化会改变设计形态，\r\n增加更多细节。设计师选用塑料材料，并搭配多种颜色。这个异想天开的挂钟外形独特有趣，同时还保持了钟表\r\n最基本的功能，让使用者清晰的知晓时间变化。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1928/sabrina-fossi-freakish%E6%9E%81%E7%AE%80%E6%8C%82%E9%92%9F.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376926/2013-08-14/img_1_1376509518_c4ca4238a0b923820dcc509a6f75849b.jpg@@sabrina fossi\'s minimally designed freakish wall clock\r\nall images courtesy of sabrina fossi##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376926/2013-08-14/img_2_1376509518_c81e728d9d4c2f636f067f89cc14862c.jpg@@\r\nfreakishclock yellow##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376926/2013-08-14/img_3_1376509518_eccbc87e4b5ce2fe28308fd9f2a7baf3.jpg@@\r\nfreakishclock green##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376926/2013-08-14/img_5_1376509518_e4da3b7fbbce2345d7772b0674a318d5.jpg@@\r\nfreakishclock pois##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376926/2013-08-14/img_6_1376509518_1679091c5a880faf6fb5e6087eb1b2dc.jpg@@\r\nfreakishclock pois'),(203,'EM2N: 巴黎条纹社会住宅项目',' ## ##作为“réaménagement de la porte pouchet”的一部分，瑞士建筑事务所EM2N设计了一座独特的条纹公寓楼，灵感来源于adolf loos\r\n在1928年为josephine baker house设计的方案。与loos的方案不同的是，EM2N事务所用黑白大理石来建造立面条纹，用穿孔钢板\r\n来制作阳台扶手。在périphériques的支持下，18个建筑地块分配给了几个不同的建筑师。EM2N事务所拿到的第17和18块基地呈\r\n锐角。这个设计创造了充足的庭院区域，并让人们注意到那些狭小的空间。通过对形态的加减切削，建筑最终产生了一种晶体般\r\n的形式效果，围绕着一个种满树木的庭院。因为严格的建筑规范限制，和特殊的锐角基地，建筑有些区域在形式上比较夸张，比如\r\n角度很深的阳台空间。#### ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1927/em2n-%E5%B7%B4%E9%BB%8E%E6%9D%A1%E7%BA%B9%E7%A4%BE%E4%BC%9A%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom00.jpg@@EM2N draws from adolf loos for parsian social housing\r\nall images courtesy of EM2N##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nthe structure becomes an expressive mark of the urban fabric \r\nall images courtesy of EM2N##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nstrict regulations led to the design of deeply recessed balconies \r\nall images courtesy of EM2N##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom03.jpg@@\r\n(left): tectonic detail\r\nimage © marcin pawlowski \r\n(right): view of the courtyard spaces \r\nimage courtesy EM2N##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom04.jpg@@\r\ninterior view \r\nall images courtesy of EM2N##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/EM2N-porte-pouchet-paris-social-housing-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nmodel of the unbuilt josephine baker house by adolf loos, wherein minimal ornamentation is used to direct lines of sight around the building\'s corners'),(204,'marte marte architects: 山地景观地标alfenz大桥',' ## ## ##\r\n由marte marte architects建筑事务所设计的“alfenz大桥”位于奥地利最西边的省份vorarlberg，是与德国、列支敦士登和瑞士\r\n的交界处，这个设计反应了山地景观的地质特征。这座混凝土桥横跨了ill河支流。这条河流常常会爆发洪水，展示了强大\r\n的自然之力。因此，河岸支撑了这座单跨桥梁的主要荷载。东侧的构架模仿了山脊的形状，让人们能观赏到ill河的景色。西边\r\n的实墙赋予桥梁坚实的属性，面朝交通繁忙的主干道。综合来讲，这个设计以结构逻辑和材料的有效利用为基础。从以人为本\r\n的角度来说，它为骑自行车的人和行人创造了一条沿bludenz-schruns的路线，是一个保护性的地标建筑。##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##[expand title=\"full article here\"  ngg_id=538][/expand]','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1926/marte-marte-architects-%E5%B1%B1%E5%9C%B0%E6%99%AF%E8%A7%82%E5%9C%B0%E6%A0%87alfenz%E5%A4%A7%E6%A1%A5.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/marte-marte-architects-alfenzbreucke-alfenz-bridge-designboom-01.jpg@@marte marte architects\' \'alfenz bridge\' is an alpine landmark\r\nimage © marc lins\r\nall images courtesy of marte marte architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/marte-marte-architects-alfenzbreucke-alfenz-bridge-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\na series of organic truss members are designed for material efficiency in reflection of the surrounding topography\r\nimage © marc lins##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/marte-marte-architects-alfenzbreucke-alfenz-bridge-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nprone to flooding, the load is carried to the banks by the reinforced concrete truss system\r\nimage © marc lins##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/marte-marte-architects-alfenzbreucke-alfenz-bridge-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nthe road and bridge parallel the ill river, giving safe passage to cyclists and pedestrians\r\nimage © marc lins'),(205,'隈研吾: 苏格兰V&A艺术博物馆',' ## ## ##\r\n日本建筑师隈研吾的竞赛获胜方案victoria and albert museum苏格兰中心最近获得了规划批准。这座单体建筑由两个\r\n锥体组成，偏移的形式在泰河与河岸之间建立了新的联系。由于这个项目的基地位置十分突出，所以设计方案不仅包含\r\n建筑本身，还将创造一个全新的公共空间网络，以充实原有的海港区域。最终的设计方案将公共空间延伸到水中，同时\r\n设计了一条围绕建筑蜿蜒前进的散步道。美术馆底层的多个公共广场不仅是户外展览活动的完美场所，同时还创造了一个\r\n可供当地居民和外地参观者休憩娱乐的滨水空间。## ##浏览designboom之前的报道请点击这里。##  ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1925/%E9%9A%88%E7%A0%94%E5%90%BE-%E8%8B%8F%E6%A0%BC%E5%85%B0va%E8%89%BA%E6%9C%AF%E5%8D%9A%E7%89%A9%E9%A6%86.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom00.jpg@@kengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/kengo-kuma-va-at-dundee-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nkengo kuma design for v&a at dundee gets planning green light\r\nimage © v&a dundee'),(206,'SUEP. 用传统竹子民间工艺建造的office of wickerwork',' ## ## \r\n日本福冈在快速发展的同时，优先考虑城市计划中的环境与可持续问题。这个可以回收再利用的“office of wickerwork”是由\r\n日本建筑事务所SUEP./hirokazu suemitsu+yoko suemitsu设计的，该方案同样考虑了环境和可持续问题。自然光照、能源和可回收\r\n材料是这个方案的主要元素。建筑屋顶和外墙选用半透明材料建造。首层立面被设计成一个对外开放的店面。因此在整个工作\r\n时间中，室内都由充足的自然光照。为了减少过热的日晒和刺眼的阳光，建筑师选用了可回收的雪松木板条，用传统的竹子民间\r\n工艺将它们编制起来，创造了一个遮阳板，并让光线柔和地慢射到室内。为了保持室内温度，屋顶下方安装了一个透光保温层，\r\n外墙则选用了聚碳酸酯玻璃板。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##建筑师: hirokazu suemitsu+yoko suemitsu/SUEP.位置: yame-shi , fukuoka pref.基地面积: 2,079.41㎡占地面积: 164.84㎡建筑面积:  221.37㎡结构: steel , +2','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1924/suep-%E7%94%A8%E4%BC%A0%E7%BB%9F%E7%AB%B9%E5%AD%90%E6%B0%91%E9%97%B4%E5%B7%A5%E8%89%BA%E5%BB%BA%E9%80%A0%E7%9A%84office-of-wickerwork.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-office-of-wickerwork-designboom-02.jpg@@SUEP. uses traditional bamboo folk craft in \'office of wickerwork\'\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)\r\nall images courtesy of SUEP.##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-office-of-wickerwork-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\noverlooking the main work area\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-office-of-wickerwork-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\ndetail. electric lights supplement daylight that filters through woven cedar strips\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-office-of-wickerwork-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\nmanager\'s office\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-office-of-wickerwork-designboom-01.jpg@@\r\nexterior view of the workplace\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)'),(207,'H&P architects: 可持续竹子, 泥土和石头建筑',' ## ## ##\r\n越南建筑事务所H&P architects设计的这座可持续的建造和文化中心致力于社区参与与教育。“BES（bamboo，earth和stone）\r\npavilion”位于越南河静市，利用当地材料和传统的建造方法建造。建造过程注重与使用者的交流和参与——建筑师希望通过\r\n“动手学习”的方法，让人们领会优秀设计的好处。建筑的布局方式是将几个分散的小空间围绕一个中心庭院布置，塑造了建筑\r\n周围的景观形式。入口引领人们进入一条介于两个建筑之间的狭窄通道，最终抵达开阔的中心庭院。这个方案有许多有机的设计\r\n方法，直接地示范并教授了空气动力学（通风设计），建筑物理（光的漫射）和生物学（光合作用，种植）。这些设计元素希望\r\n能影响建筑的使用者，今后以一种更加绿色环保的方式生活。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑师: h&p architects位置: ha tinh, vietnam主持建筑师: doan thanh ha & tran ngoc phuong团队: chu kim thinh承建商: hpa viet nam jsc建筑面积: 123 sqm占地: 18m x 13m完工: 2013. 8## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1922/hp-architects-%E5%8F%AF%E6%8C%81%E7%BB%AD%E7%AB%B9%E5%AD%90-%E6%B3%A5%E5%9C%9F%E5%92%8C%E7%9F%B3%E5%A4%B4%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/HP-architects-BES-pavilion-designboom00.jpg@@H&P architects: sustainable bamboo, earth and stone pavilion\r\nall images courtesy of H&P architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_6_1376359582_1599e5539bab2131c5b7aa3db4321869.jpg@@\r\nBES pavilion by H&P architects features an arrangement of separate huts clustered around a central courtyard space##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_3_1376359582_4c7fcaad0169a7f32ca1d189e2c0764e.jpg@@\r\nthe entrance leads one along a narrow pathway between two structures, eventually opening out to the interior courtyard##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_7_1376359582_366b8b1a7d4a134b6ddba660f4b1f2e7.jpg@@\r\n the pavilions were constructed using traditional building methods##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_8_1376359582_ce04ed04dd9bf9e598c7cdfc3afb971c.jpg@@\r\nview of the entrance\'s pathway between two structures which leads to the interior\'s open courtyard##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_9_1376359582_7d54b9f727c17980a5a5127404639c7c.jpg@@\r\naerial view of the central courtyard space##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_2_1376359582_cb63b20ed3aa9cf9733f7c9283fd9587.jpg@@\r\nexterior view of the pavilion\'s huts, which are built around sustainable principles##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_10_1376359582_81c141bf0c5ee0c529a7a344cd709d9d.jpg@@\r\nview looking through to the central courtyard##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_11_1376359582_c1602c432fffce2969427c408b4eb584.JPG@@\r\nnighttime view of the transparent pavilions with screens open towards the street##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_5_1376359582_986a9801fff7a70ec6e36426b38aca4f.jpg@@\r\nnighttime perspective from the street##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_4_1376359582_5f635f6de90fb27b421da69a04732902.jpg@@\r\naerial view showing the pavilion\'s central arrangement on the site##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/371135/2013-08-13/img_12_1376359582_c16d5e952f7fddd3a8e42415d56368c6.jpg@@\r\nplan and view of the hut\'s internal space'),(208,'isabelle dalle: 数字解剖肖像',' ## ## ##法国数字艺术家isabelle dalle最近创作了一系列解剖肖像。她的创作收到传统医学期刊艺术的影响，参考了身体各个部位\r\n的特定计数法，详细的描绘了肌肉和骨骼的阴影。这些当代的彩色拼贴画将动物、翅膀、以及深海生物与肖像并置，让它们\r\n从脸部和人体中突出出来。isabelle dalle的作品通过古典与当代插画的拼接，展示了人类形态不和谐的一面。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1923/isabelle-dalle-%E6%95%B0%E5%AD%97%E8%A7%A3%E5%89%96%E8%82%96%E5%83%8F.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Isabelle-Dalle-designboom-30.jpg@@isabelle dalle digital anatomy portraits \r\nall images courtesy of isabelle dalle##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Isabelle-Dalle-designboom-21.jpg@@\r\n\'we better fly\'##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Isabelle-Dalle-designboom-22.jpg@@\r\n\'the fish tank...\'##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Isabelle-Dalle-designboom-32.jpg@@ \r\n\'happy bird day\'##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Isabelle-Dalle-designboom-37.jpg@@\r\n\'la jeune fille et la mort\''),(209,'design blitz: 帕洛阿尔托skype总部',' ## ## ##design blitz建筑事务所将一座空闲的仓库改造成skype帕洛阿尔托总部，它们对旧仓库进行了几层翻修，削减了许多不必要的元素，\r\n只留下最核心的部分，最终设计成一个条理清晰的工作空间。同心圆形的空间布局支持了员工之间的合作、集中和沉思。一个中心\r\n走廊贯穿了整个建筑，而最吵闹的空间则被安排在同心圆的中心。建筑师设计了一种可以独立支撑的天花板结构，搭配通常用在长\r\n跨度建筑中的波纹金属板。这些天花板结构包围了空间，建筑师想，“它们还能做些其它什么事呢？”，随后添加了降噪材料，完善\r\n了天花板结构。为了将董事会议室与其它空间区别开，建筑师选用葡萄酒桶上的木条，将它们装饰在会议室的外墙上，与北加利福尼亚\r\n的葡萄酒之乡形成呼应。在会议室、公共工作区和非正式聚会区域之间设置了一系列可移动家具、“Skype-its”或其它用于头脑风暴的\r\n可移动白板。在同心圆空间的外围是独立的工作台，员工们可以充分的享受自然光照。在改造过程中，原有仓库的天花板被拆除，仅留下\r\n最基本的构造，为整个空间增添了仓库一样的感觉。自主房间、局部照明和趣味家具的置入，增加了人尺度元素，间接的色彩搭配和空间\r\n开放性为员工创造了合作与创新的大背景。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1921/design-blitz-%E5%B8%95%E6%B4%9B%E9%98%BF%E5%B0%94%E6%89%98skype%E6%80%BB%E9%83%A8.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-01.jpg@@design blitz: skype headquarters in palo alto\r\nall photographs by matthew millman and hoffman chrisman\r\nall images courtesy of design blitz##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nmovable furniture allows employees to arrange seating as necessary to facilitate productivity\r\n ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nskype pod##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nthe design is characterized by a series of space for creative thinking \r\nimage © matthew millman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\ngame room##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nas a company that facilitates communication, there are many different types of collaborative spaces within the office##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\nmap of the USA in lights lines the main corridor\r\nimage © matthew millman##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/design-blitz-skype-headquarters-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\nreception lobby'),(210,'SUEP.: 森林吊床美术馆',' ## ##日本建筑事务所SUEP./hirokazu suemitsu + yoko suemitsu设计的这个拥有悬浮屋顶结构的艺术画廊像一个悬挂在森林中的\r\n吊床。 这座建筑位于日本福冈的一座新公园中，周围是巨大的樟脑树。为了将自然景观与室内空间相融合，与树木相交的\r\n屋顶和地面板被切割掉了，加强了建筑独特的形式感。##屋顶平面和缓地向下弯曲，顺着重力作用形成悬链形——与吊床的悬挂形式相类似。屋顶和地面都采用了钢结构和混凝土\r\n楼板，树木间的剪力墙用来支撑这些水平楼板。建筑外部形式将室内外空间融为一体，屋顶结构则作为室内阳台的遮蔽物——\r\n建筑两侧都保持开放，欢迎公园里的人们进入室内。参观者不仅可以欣赏到艺术作品，还能体验到舒适惬意的居住氛围，好似\r\n躺在森林里的吊床中。##\r\n这座美术馆就在隈研吾设计的“kyushu geibun kan main building”旁边。浏览这个文化中心方案的更多信息请点击这里。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑师: hirokazu suemitsu + yoko suemitsu/SUEP.位置: fukuoka chikugo基地面积: 12,914.74 square meters占地面积: 414.46 square meters建筑面积: 334.77 square meters结构: steel plate concrete one-story building设计: 2009.10 - 2010.10建造: 2011.08 - 2012.12','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1920/suep-%E6%A3%AE%E6%9E%97%E5%90%8A%E5%BA%8A%E7%BE%8E%E6%9C%AF%E9%A6%86.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom00.jpg@@forest hammock gallery by SUEP.\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)\r\nall images courtesy of SUEP.##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nview of the art gallery\'s internal patio and the web-like cut outs of the building\'s form\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nthe suspended roof structure gives the impression of a hammock hanging in a forest\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe curved roof gently falls downwards, similar to the hanging motion of a hammock\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom04.jpg@@\r\ndetail of the suspended roof structure and support column\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nconcept diagram showing the curved cut-outs in the roof and floor plate\r\nimage © SUEP.##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nsite plan\r\nimage © SUEP.##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/hammock-gallery-suep-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nsection\r\nimage © SUEP.'),(211,'daniel libeskind: 杜塞尔多夫ko-bogen大厦动工建设',' ## ##由studio daniel libeskind建筑事务所设计的这座全新的六层建筑“kö-bogen”最近开始动工建设，并将于今年完工。这个项目\r\n将购物、散步和工作三者结合，它共有432,300平方英尺的办公空间和零售中心，位于德国杜塞尔多夫——基地就在城区和周围\r\n公园景观的分界线上。巨大的绿色屋顶和人行散步道把基地与shadowplat、hofgarte宫廷花园连接起来。这个项目希望将自然与\r\n建筑物融为一体，立面上被切割的部分将作为可居住的绿色空间。对比鲜明的几何形立面作为流动性的曲线元素与尖锐的三角形\r\n边缘并置在一起。这座多功能中心占据了城市两个街区，由一个两层的空中桥梁和屋顶平台连接。两个街区之间的开放庭院进一步\r\n融合了建筑与景观，同时为室内空间提供了大量自然光照。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## 全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑面积: 40,165 sq.m (base design) 13,547 sq.m (underground parking ) 38,097 sq.m (alternative design)完工: 2013业主: die developer结构工程: nai nagaraj ingenieure设备/电气: winter ingenieure土木工程: ingenieurbüro wendt立面: murphy facade studio + infacon成本控制总承建商: zechbau gmbh建筑物理: graner + partner | ingenieure立面顾问: murphy facade studio + infacon## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1919/daniel-libeskind-%E6%9D%9C%E5%A1%9E%E5%B0%94%E5%A4%9A%E5%A4%ABko-bogen%E5%A4%A7%E5%8E%A6%E5%8A%A8%E5%B7%A5%E5%BB%BA%E8%AE%BE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom01.jpg@@daniel libeskind: ko-bogen düsseldorf under construction \r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom00.jpg@@\r\nrendering of the mixed-used development \'kö-bogen\' which is currently under construction\r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe new development is built over two city blocks, connected by an overhead two-story bridge with roof terraces\r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nthe six-story development is a combined destination for shopping, walking and working\r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom04.jpg@@\r\ndaniel libeskind: ko-bogen under construction \r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nthe facade features contrasting geometric shapes, blending natural and built elements \r\nimage © archimation##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nmodel of \'kö-bogen\' by studio daniel libeskind\r\nimage © SDL##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nmodel showing the permeated green cuts in the exterior form\r\nimage © SDL##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ko-bogen-daniel-libeskind-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nrendering showing an overview of the site\r\nimage © archimation'),(212,'mark mawson: 水下绘画摄影作品',' ## ## ##英国摄影师mark mawson在他最新的系列作品“aqueous II - the sequel”中探索了色彩、墨水和水三种材料的结合。这些电子合成图像捕捉了物体在水下的效果——各种不同颜色的液体在水中混合、滴落、旋转。摄影师拍摄了这些凝固\r\n的动作，捕捉了汹涌的、催眠般的水下形态，以及巨大黑色背景下的漩涡和涟漪。这些摄影作品描绘了各种不同的幻影——\r\n沉没的蘑菇云在空间中膨胀，活跃的水母一样的形态，以及幽灵般的色彩线条。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1918/mark-mawson-%E6%B0%B4%E4%B8%8B%E7%BB%98%E7%94%BB%E6%91%84%E5%BD%B1%E4%BD%9C%E5%93%81.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-14.jpg@@underwater paint photography by mark mawsonall images courtesy of mark mawson##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-16.jpg@@\r\nthe pastel pink paint creates a silhouette that resembles a jellyfish##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-18.jpg@@\r\nelectric blue paint streams downwards through the water##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-15.jpg@@\r\na smokey blue shape arises from a mass of foggy paint##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-19.jpg@@\r\na long thin line of white paint stems up from a mass of paint##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-21.jpg@@\r\na small droplet of red paint balloons into a tiny mushroom-like form##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-22.jpg@@\r\nthe submerged pigment creates a form that resembles a tree, with thin colored branches and stems##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Mark-Mawson-acqueous-designboom-13.jpg@@\r\na thick cloud of red and yellow paint surging upwards from the center of the paint spill'),(213,'atrium studio: 文化+运动中心改造设计',' ## ## ##\r\n斯洛伐克建筑事务所atrium studio将这个热交换设施转化成一座文化和运动中心，这个项目也是 EHMK 2013的一部分。\r\n建筑位于斯洛伐克nad jazerom的一处住宅区，三角形的外立面，用一种戏剧化的攀岩墙，将建筑拓展到公共空间中。这座交换中心有五个不同的，相互连通的楼层，建筑师把它们全部转化成展厅空间——每层都有一种不同功能。另外一个\r\n隐蔽的屋顶空间包含四棵大树和一间巨大的休息室，给出那关着提供了一个休息放松的区域。这座文化运动中心向周围的\r\n工业类型建筑延伸。原有的热交换设施被一个大胆的几何形立面包裹——折叠的三角形立面重新定义了建筑的外观。外立面\r\n有些部分被裁切掉，露出了内部窗户，进一步地展示了新的改造设计。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ##项目信息:## ##日期: 2011投资方: city košice, european capital of culture 2013建筑面积: 180 m²位置: važecká street, košice','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1917/atrium-studio-%E6%96%87%E5%8C%96%E8%BF%90%E5%8A%A8%E4%B8%AD%E5%BF%83%E6%94%B9%E9%80%A0%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom03.jpg@@atrium studio: heat exchanger turned culture + sports centerimage © atriumstudio.sk##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe development was part of a project for the EHMK 2013, the european capital of cultureimage © lubo stacho##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom00.jpg@@\r\n the existing building was wrapped with a bold geometric facadeimage © atrium studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom04.jpg@@the angular exterior form features a large climbing wallimage © atrium studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nthe structure stands out within its surrounding context of industrial-type buildingsimage © atrium studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nfolded triangular shapes create a large climbing wall on the building\'s exteriorimage © atrium studio##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/heat-exchanger-vazecka-atrium-studio-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nthe center has five different interconnected floors that have all been turned into gallery spacesimage © lubo stacho'),(214,'kjellgren kaminsky: 电动车太阳能充电站','solar powered charging station for cars by kjellgren kaminsky architecture\r\nall images courtesy of kjellgren kaminsky architecture## ## ## ##随着瑞典电动汽车数量的不断增长，哥德堡市的交通部门委托当地建筑事务所kjellgren kamisky architecture设计一个可持续的\r\n个人交通系统。建筑师最终提出的方案是一个为电动车设计的太阳能充电站，自行车和小摩托车停放处，等候区，自行车修理铺，户外\r\n体育馆，咖啡吧和信息亭——所有地方都有wifi信号。这个设计尚处于概念探讨阶段，但这个可以提供能源，同时最大限度的减少碳排放量\r\n的建筑将对城市环境和景观产生重要的影响。这座建筑在为电动车充电的同时为司机们提供了多种资源。当地的木材材料为建筑创造了具有\r\n伸展性的可持续化城市愿景。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1916/kjellgren-kaminsky-%E7%94%B5%E5%8A%A8%E8%BD%A6%E5%A4%AA%E9%98%B3%E8%83%BD%E5%85%85%E7%94%B5%E7%AB%99.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom00.jpg@@\r\nlocally sourced wood completes the tilted construction and posits a solution to the urban problem of personal transportation energy sources ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom.jpg@@\r\npatrons can charge their car with energy harnessed from the PV panel studded roof ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nplan views ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nplan views ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nconceptual sketch of the structure ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nsketches of the tilted form ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nwood truss construction articulated in a sketch ##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/KKA-solar-powered-charging-station-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nsketch shows the architecture in context '),(215,'iwan baan: SANAA设计的vitra campus factory建筑摄影图片',' ## ## \r\n今年年初，SANAA设计的“vitra factory building”（点击这里浏览designboom之前的报道）建造完成，这个项目于2010年\r\n开工建设。作为瑞士家具品牌vitra在德国莱茵河畔威尔城厂区的展示场所、生产区和仓库，“vitra factory building”\r\n拥有一个圆形的平面，并由两个相邻的半圆形混凝土壳体组成。建筑外立面包裹了一层特殊的波形丙烯板，没有完全的接触\r\n地面，让这座在整个厂区中面积最大的建筑看起来好像漂浮在空中。##\r\n著名建筑摄影师iwan baan为这座建筑拍摄了一组照片，经过全面的观察和拍摄，为我们提供了一系列前所未见的视角。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1915/iwan-baan-sanaa%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E7%9A%84vitra-campus-factory%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91%E6%91%84%E5%BD%B1%E5%9B%BE%E7%89%87.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SANAA-vitra-campus-factory-building-photography-by-iwan-baan1.jpg@@SANAA: VITRA campus factory photography by iwan baan\r\nimage © iwan baan##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SANAA-vitra-campus-factory-building-photography-by-iwan-baan-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nthe \'vitra campus factory\' photographed by iwan baan\r\nimage © iwan baan##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SANAA-vitra-campus-factory-building-photography-by-iwan-baan-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\naerial view of the vitra campus with the newly completed SANAA-designed factory building \r\nimage © iwan baan##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SANAA-vitra-campus-factory-building-photography-by-iwan-baan-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nview of the vitra campus in the context of its countryside location\r\nimage © iwan baan'),(216,'zaha hadid: 迈阿密住宅项目one thousand museum',' ## ## ##zaha hadid最近公布了两张她在美国设计的首座住宅建筑的图片。这个60层的高级住宅项目，将于2014年完工，重塑迈阿密\r\n的城市天际线。“one thousand museum”沿主干道biscayne boulevard建造，预计将超过700英尺，建筑结构会穿在表皮之上。蜿蜒\r\n的外露骨骼是建筑的最大特色，同时将突出的阳台隐藏起来。利用zaha hadid独特的建筑形式语言，这个项目有助于迈阿密成为\r\n成熟的国际大都市和文化中心。预计公寓的价格在900美元到1400美元每平方英尺之间，因此每套公寓的价格大概在400万美元\r\n到1500万美元之间。复式公寓的价格在3000万美元到5000万美元之间，以满足迈阿密超豪华住宅市场的需求。## ##更新:我们更新了2013年5月29日刊登的文章，增添了两张“one thousand museum”项目的新图片。浏览这个项目的更多信息请点击这里。## ## ## ## ## ##the exoskeleton is part of a greater concept of melding structure and skin \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ## ## ##the sinuous form in the oceanfront skyline context \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ##view out from the tower \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ##the glittering cityscape is emboldened by the honest, albeit conceptually rich, architectural form \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ##interiors reframe the southern urban metropolis with curves \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ##interior view \r\nimage © one thousand museum## ## ##the architectural language is a synthesis of form and structure \r\nimage © one thousand museum##','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1914/zaha-hadid-%E8%BF%88%E9%98%BF%E5%AF%86%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AEone-thousand-museum.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-miami-designboom-01.jpg@@zaha hadid: one thousand museum brings boldness to the miami skyline\r\nimage © zaha hadid architects, rendering by catapult 13##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-miami-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\na new rendering reveals the \'one thousand museum\' tower by zaha hadid at night\r\nimage © zaha hadid architects, rendering by catapult 13##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom02.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom00.jpg@@\r\nzaha hadid\'s \'one thousand museum\' tower along in the context of the miami skyline\r\nimage © one thousand museum##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom01.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom06.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom07.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom03.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom04.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/zaha-hadid-one-thousand-museum-designboom05.jpg@@'),(217,'janne kyttanen：cubify可下载3D打印高跟鞋',' ## ##janne kyttanen设计了一个3D打印高跟鞋系列，使用者可以从网上免费下载，连夜打印，第二天就可以穿上新鞋。\r\n kyttanen为3D打印网站cubify设计了一系列产品，可以用cubeX打印机制作出来。消费者可以在网上免费获得数字模型，\r\n挑选型号和颜色，然后用6到7个小时的时间打印出来。这一系列共有四种不同风格：facet；拥有几何形构造，macedonia；\r\n厚厚的鞋底上设计了许多孔隙，leaf；带有树叶形状的图案，classic；简洁的楔形高跟鞋。## ## ## ## ##\r\n\r\nintroducing cubify\'s first ever 3D printed shoes\r\nvideo courtesy of cubify## ## \r\n“虽然我对女人和女鞋知之甚少，但我非常喜爱他们。如果我的女友可以每天换一双不同的鞋子，那就更好了。现在这变成了现实。\r\n女人们可以晚上3D打印，制作自己的鞋子，在第二天早上穿一双新鞋出门。” -- janne kyttanen## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1912/janne-kyttanen%EF%BC%9Acubify%E5%8F%AF%E4%B8%8B%E8%BD%BD3d%E6%89%93%E5%8D%B0%E9%AB%98%E8%B7%9F%E9%9E%8B.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cubify-designboom.jpg@@cubify\'s downloadable 3D printed shoes by janne kyttanenimages courtesy of cubify##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-03.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nthe macedonia high heel shoe##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\ncolorful variations of the macedonia shoe##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\na pair of blue classic shoes##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-01.jpg@@\r\norange facet shoes##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/3D-printed-shoes-cubify-CubeX-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\nleaf shoes in the cubeX 3D printer'),(218,'SUEP. ：双层屋顶住宅',' ## ## ##\r\n日本建筑事务所SUEP./hirokazu suemitsu + yoko suemitsu设计的这座悬链曲线住宅“double roof house”将相互分离的空间连接\r\n起来，还可以起到遮阳作用。建筑位于日本山口县一处住宅区中，周围都是低矮的小住宅，没有大面积的阴影。这座单层建筑有\r\n两个屋顶，由五个盒子体量组成，每个盒子都有特定的功能。每个不同区域都安装了“sudare”（芦苇帘），可以减少50%的阳光\r\n直射。两个体量之间的小缝隙让漫射光线可以穿透建筑，照射到室内。建筑依附基地地形，舒适地坐落在景观之中。##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑师: hirokazu suemitsu + yoko suemitsu/SUEP.\r\n位置: yamaguchi prefecture基地面积: 1,326.1 sq m占地面积: 235.2 sq m建筑面积: 235.2 sq m结构: wooden bungalow## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1913/suep-%EF%BC%9A%E5%8F%8C%E5%B1%82%E5%B1%8B%E9%A1%B6%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom01.jpg@@SUEP. double roof house features a floating reed screen\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)\r\nall images courtesy of SUEP.##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nthe one story building consists of two roofs, which visually connects the separate spaces\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom03.jpg@@\r\ninterior view of the kitchen and living spaces\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nview of the entrance underneath the floating double roof\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom05.jpg@@\r\ninterior view of \'double roof house\' by SUEP.\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom00.jpg@@\r\nnight view\r\nimage © kai nakamura (中村絵)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nrendering##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nsite plan##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SUEP-double-roof-house-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nplan and section'),(219,'ABA：邦迪海滩住宅',' ## ## ##\r\n澳大利亚建筑事务所andrew burges architects在悉尼邦迪海滩设计了这座内部呈几何形式的住宅建筑，它向外部庭院开放。\r\n室内空间经过细致地的组合，创造了一系列开放的空隙和视线交流。建筑师设计了一个两层的方盒子体量，让住宅避开周边\r\n建筑，给屋主提供一个私密的居住空间。与周边内向型的住宅建筑不同，这座有趣的住宅，每个楼层都向天空和庭院开放。建筑\r\n采用胶合板与混凝土材料，二层有一条木板带，包裹了窗户和格栅。这座沙滩住宅在保持了必要私密性的同时，让居住者可以亲近\r\n户外景观。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个项目来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1911/aba%EF%BC%9A%E9%82%A6%E8%BF%AA%E6%B5%B7%E6%BB%A9%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ABA-beach-house-bondi-designboom00.jpg@@plywood beach house retreat in bondi by ABA\r\nall images courtesy of andrew burges architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ABA-beach-house-bondi-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nstreet view##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375877/2013-08-03/img_9_1375533432_c6e138ab6458f1fce1d2111bea9357bb.jpg@@\r\nupper level strip of screens and windows##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ABA-beach-house-bondi-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nview showing external materials used with timber screened windows +view of the courtyard entry##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/img_8_1375533432_47d9a8cbe135aecc86514c15cb250759.jpg@@\r\n central skylight overhead - looking towards the rear garden##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ABA-beach-house-bondi-designboom05.jpg@@ \r\nview of skylight that connects both levels to the garden##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ABA-beach-house-bondi-designboom06.jpg@@\r\ninternal geometry consists of voids and framed view shafts + view looking towards the rear garden from entry##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375877/2013-08-03/img_5_1375533432_a6a72dd4fd74c6f0592512c69ea468f5.jpg@@\r\nthe garage doubles as a home office and workshop##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375877/2013-08-03/img_11_1375533432_6749080141ba26f79f2392ea113536a6.jpg@@\r\nmodel studies of internal geometry##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375877/2013-08-03/img_12_1375533432_e5dd5bac98f5eabd1dfa198d5b11a7fe.jpg@@\r\nplans and section'),(220,'UA architects：shirasagi博物馆',' ## ##\r\n由UA architects设计的这座白色曲线型博物馆位于日本宇都宫，基地介于两条南北向的大路交叉口。这个设计挑战了公共\r\n与私有土地所有权的界限，这条连续的路径已经被当地人走了30多年了。基地的主人希望能在这条公共道路上展示自己收藏\r\n的艺术作品。一个10平方米的书房和展厅采用当地传统材料，覆盖了一层白色的、水平面板。为了将人们从街道引入室内，建筑\r\n围绕着基地卷曲。极简的建筑星矢包含一个圆形的、开放空间，无论是周围景观还是展示的艺术作品都能被完全的欣赏到。建筑\r\n简洁的形式以及从街道到室内的空间流动性，加强了整个地区的环境体验。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##项目信息:## ##建筑类型: 博物馆基地面积: 464.80 square meters (140.60 square meters)建筑面积: 73.00 square meters (22.08 square meters)位置: utsunomiya shimotahara town 1758-1设计和监理: shoji oshio + UA Tokyo, utsunomiya Off## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1910/ua-architects%EF%BC%9Ashirasagi%E5%8D%9A%E7%89%A9%E9%A6%86.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_001-1.jpg@@UA architects curves pathway through shirasagi museum\r\nall images courtesy of UA architects##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_002.jpg@@\r\nthe entrance to the study and exhibition room faces the middle of the tunnel-like passage##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_007.jpg@@\r\nthe museum sits on a circular passageway##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_005.jpg@@\r\nthe structure curves along the road, with the outer wall leading in a circular motion along the passageway##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_011.jpg@@\r\na 10 meter square study and exhibition room was built from traditional local materials with white, horizontal cladding##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/designboom_UA-architects_shirasagi-museum_008.jpg@@\r\nframed view shafts cast bold, direct light into the interior space'),(221,'de blacam & meagher architects: san lorenzo north on the green',' ## ## \r\n爱尔兰建筑事务所de blacam & meagher architects最近完成了“san lorenzo north”，这是一座位于葡萄牙阿尔加维金塔湖的豪华别墅。\r\n白色的建筑由一系列直线形体量组成，在花园一侧形成一个纪念性的门廊。基地南侧较低处则创造了一个私人入口。与之相对比\r\n的是，南立面上设有巨大的滑动玻璃门，与两层通告的走廊相连。宽敞的平台为居住者提供了重组的户外休闲空间，可以尽情享受\r\n葡萄牙的日光。中间空间的比例较低，创造了更加亲切的氛围。埋地式游泳池将厨房和餐厅延伸到户外庭院；水池周边是就餐区，\r\n重新定义了建筑边界。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## 全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1909/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-on-the-green.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-01M.jpg@@de blacam & meagher architects: san lorenzo north quinta do lago algarve portugal\r\nimage courtesy of quinta do lago##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\na series of rectilinear volumes step back toward the back yard, growing in proportion until becoming double height at the living room, which expands outdoors to the covered terrace with large sliding glass doors\r\nimage courtesy of quinta do lago##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nan outdoor dining area defines the edge of the pool terrace in the intervention by de blacam & meagher architects\r\nimage courtesy of quinta do lago##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\n(left): the living space extends outdoors with extensive terraces\r\n(right): evening sun highlights the adjacent fairway\r\nimages courtesy of quinta do lago##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\nthe low ceiling of the kitchen and dining create an intimate atmosphere\r\nimage courtesy of quinta do lago##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/de-blacam-meagher-architects-san-lorenzo-north-quinta-do-lago-algarve-portugal-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nthe spacious double height living room balances light and transparency\r\nimage courtesy of quinta do lago'),(222,'studioFAR：pinball桌面图钉配件','  ## ##这个“pinball”图钉配件让我们在墙上展示作品时获得更多乐趣。“pinball”是美国studioFAR设计的。这个硅胶塑膜图钉配件\r\n用一种聪明的方式来存放土登。不管是用图钉展示艺术作品、概念或是发表，它都能为人们提供更有趣的合作体验。每个pinball\r\n能放最多60个图钉，不用的时候，就是一个有趣的桌面小配件。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## \r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1908/studiofar%EF%BC%9Apinball%E6%A1%8C%E9%9D%A2%E5%9B%BE%E9%92%89%E9%85%8D%E4%BB%B6.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_2_1375311228_70a24073784b34d4ac170ed417df3065.jpg@@pin pin pass: pushpin pinball storage by studioFAR\r\nall images courtesy of studioFAR##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_1_1375311228_a3e886ba7f2168f05bcda7fd9b1a064e.jpg@@\r\npushpins removed##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_6_1375311228_c81952c178d63b7fab25db0058fc340e.jpg@@\r\nsculptural desktop accessory##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_5_1375311228_946c9e30fd59911d6c358b1d5a368238.jpg@@\r\n\'pinball\' by studioFAR - a creative pushpin storage device##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_3_1375311228_3cd496e3669e590ebea5710c13919a57.jpg@@\r\npinball can be passed around to help make presentations more fun and relaxed##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/376364/2013-07-31/img_4_1375311228_4ff7aba9864073d40c7df98ea7801f60.jpg@@\r\nan interactive piece for work presentations'),(223,'国家地理杂志2013年摄影大赛优胜作品',' ## ## ##国家地理杂志最近公布了2013 traveler photo contest旅行者摄影大赛的获奖作品。 今年是第25届竞赛，共收到了来自世界各地\r\n超过15,500份参赛作品，题材多样，共分四个单元：旅行肖像，户外风景，地域风情和自然瞬间。\r\n ##这些摄影作品拍摄于世界的各个角落，从缅甸古都蒲甘到犹他州的大峡谷。这些图片揭示了地球大自然的方方面面——自然的\r\n人类瞬间，动物，以及地球上一些最美地区的惊人风景。评委会以7项评审标准从所有参赛作品中挑选出前三名。优胜作品会刊登\r\n在