为一件城市家具，立面上透明\r\n的玻璃立面包裹了新的商业空间，从室外可以看到原有的老建筑。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1889/archinauten%EF%BC%9Afaux-pli-gourmet%E8%B6%85%E5%B8%82%E6%89%A9%E5%BB%BA%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faux-pli-archinauten-designboom01.jpg@@\'faux pli\' gourmet supermarket extension by archinauten\r\nall images courtesy of archinauten##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faux-pli-archinauten-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nsouth-west view in twilight, the facade merges into the surrounding promenade##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faux-pli-archinauten-designboom03.jpg@@\r\n the extension is an enlargement to the existing gourmet spar supermarket##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375953/2013-07-22/img_5_1374499965_833446119237a1212af6da7d31e0f73c.jpg@@\r\nfacade in public use##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faux-pli-archinauten-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nthe wooden bench seating allows people to enjoy the view of the lake from the other side##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375953/2013-07-22/img_3_1374499965_840328b47fbd07bd8d49b0f3c55e1c3c.jpg@@\r\n\'faux pli\' is located at the bank of gmunden, lake traunsee, upper austria##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375953/2013-07-22/img_6_1374499965_94f128b2036de599c66e2d291e232aad.jpg@@\r\nview of the lake and spar supermarket in its context##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375953/2013-07-22/img_4_1374499965_363a567eae8a0cc13e4b8a8512424078.jpg@@\r\ndetail of the precast concrete components with view through to supermarket\'s interior##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/faux-pli-archinauten-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nlighting detail##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375953/2013-07-22/img_10_1374499965_909c3aa4f1a286126d283be93a00b479.jpg@@\r\nsite'),(302,'david horan：美学 + 功能的装饰家具系列',' ## ## ##\r\n伦敦设计师david horan设计的“the ornamental furniture project”中所有元素都被扭曲。设计师试图将美学形式与功能紧密\r\n结合到一起，所有设计选择都由形式美学所决定。这一系列包括一张桌子和椅子，这些家具都设有巨大的松木桌椅腿，\r\n它与轻薄的胶合板桌面或椅面直接相连。这种对比创造了强劲的，无需底部支撑结构的独立设计体。因此设计的外形\r\n与功能就一种无法言说的形式紧密结合起来。桌面和椅面上涂了一层细石墨涂料，小茶几使用了铝合金材料，搭配大胆\r\n的橘金色涂料。另外还有意见功能模糊的家具配件，它既是一个小茶几，也能当作小凳使用，材料选用了松木板和黑色\r\n石墨涂料。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\r\n这个设计来自于designboom的专栏\'DIY submissions\'，我们欢迎广大读者积极投稿，上传自己的设计作品。\r\n浏览更多读者投稿请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/4/view/1888/david-horan%EF%BC%9A%E7%BE%8E%E5%AD%A6-%E5%8A%9F%E8%83%BD%E7%9A%84%E8%A3%85%E9%A5%B0%E5%AE%B6%E5%85%B7%E7%B3%BB%E5%88%97.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ornamental-furniture-david-horandesignboom01.jpg@@david horan\'s ornamental furniture embraces beauty + function\r\nall images courtesy of david horane##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/271688/2013-07-23/img_2_1374593283_a2f660690bb66bbef316b03e4c81d9f1.jpg@@\r\ndesk with solid pine legs and a graphite pigment finish##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ornamental-furniture-david-horandesignboom02.jpg@@\r\nchair - the contrasting appearance and function of the pieces are inexplicably combined##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ornamental-furniture-david-horandesignboom03.jpg@@\r\nanodized side table##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ornamental-furniture-david-horandesignboom04.jpg@@\r\nstool / side table'),(303,'herzog & de meuron：flinders street station竞赛设计方案',' ## ## ##herzog and de meuron与HASSELL合作参加了flinders street车站设计竞赛，他们提出了一个拱形的建筑设计方案。设计团队\r\n将拱形元素复制，形成图案形式，将光线折射到重组后的室内大厅中。竞赛要求对这一历史建筑进行保护；同时要将动态的\r\n交通流线引入到基地中。现存的室内空间中公共区域基本都被封闭，建筑师引入了一系列咖啡厅、酒吧、零售商店和其它\r\n服务设施将原本封闭的公共空间重新打开。原有建筑的历史元素被原封不动的保留下来，室内舞厅、体育馆和附近旧办公大楼\r\n的房间都没做改动。这个方案还设计了一个巨大的公共广场和露天剧场，让车站向河岸开放——为人们提供了休息、表演和日常\r\n活动的场所。沿建筑立面设置的散步道也打破了基地的线形配置。这个方案为墨尔本带来了一个全新的文化设施以及一座世界级的\r\n海洋和当代艺术博物馆。建筑独特的拱顶结构——原本是作为当地集市的储存空间使用的——通过新设计的步行路线，拱顶将车站\r\n广场的西南两端重新连接起来。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1887/herzog-de-meuron%EF%BC%9Aflinders-street-station%E7%AB%9E%E8%B5%9B%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E6%96%B9%E6%A1%88.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom00.jpg@@herzog & de meuron propose vaulted flinders street station  \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron \r\nall images courtesy of flinder  street station design competition##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom01.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom02.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom03.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom04.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom05.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom06.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom07.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom08.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom09.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom10.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom11.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom12.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom13.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/herzog-and-de-meuron-flinders-street-station-proposal-designboom15.jpg@@\r\nherzog & de meuron unveil flinder street station proposal \r\nimage © herzog & de meuron'),(304,'SHJworks: 丹麦音乐节临时建筑the velvet state',' ## ## SHJworks将悬链曲线板复制、旋转、放大，组成了一系列形式多样的壳体“the velvet state”，这个临时的建筑由10个原型组成，\r\n探索了感性的社会，是为丹麦2013roskilde festival设计的。 从1972年以来，丹麦roskilde festival促进了许多音乐和艺术创作上的\r\n国际文化体验。在这一方案中，建筑师与艺术家协同工作，创造了一个有时限的装置，并通过这个设计来探索arnold van gennep\r\n的限界概念。在建筑构造上， 我们可以看到艺术家与建筑师之间的合作，树脂缝线将胶合木板像缝衣服一样组装在一起，内部是\r\n气支撑作用的金属拱梁。794平方米的空间有五个后台区，由12个化妆间组成，分别是“the ring”，“the ridge”，“the reactor”，\r\n“the barn”和“the dressing room”。在中心“the courtyard”区是丹麦fiction pimps和英国剧团collective unconscious。“the stage”则作为\r\n开放的圆环和中心围合区之间的空地。这个设计让世界各地的艺术家在这一空间奉献具有创造力的表演，同时它也为参观者创造\r\n全新的体验。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。## ## ##项目信息:## ##项目名称: the velvet stage面积: 794 平方米建筑师: SHJworks 设计团队:主持建筑师: simon hjermind jensen现场建筑师: christian bøcker sørensen助理建筑师: henri käpynen 助理现场建筑师: mads bryld sørensen执行顾问: fiction pimps and collective unconscious','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1886/shjworks-%E4%B8%B9%E9%BA%A6%E9%9F%B3%E4%B9%90%E8%8A%82%E4%B8%B4%E6%97%B6%E5%BB%BA%E7%AD%91the-velvet-state.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-01.jpg@@SHJworks: \'the velvet state\' is a stage for creative exploration\r\nphoto by simon hjermind jensen\r\nall images courtesy of SHJworks##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\nthe architecture was designed with collaborative input from the performers who would use the space\r\nphoto by lasse ryberg##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-03.jpg@@\r\nseven components make up the construct; pictured here: the ridge\r\nphoto by simon hjermind jensen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nthe main performance happens in the courtyard\r\nphoto by christian böcker sörensen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-05.jpg@@\r\na single dome \'stage\' opens to the ring for musical performances\r\nphoto by simon hjermind jensen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nat night the stage is illuminated, and the brilliant harlequin finish is unveiled\r\nphoto by christian böcker sörensen##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SHJworks-the-velvet-state-denmark-designboom-07.jpg@@\r\nin the last 30 years, the roskilde foundation has donated almost all of it proceeds, nearly €25.4 million, to charity\r\nphoto by christian böcker sörensen'),(305,'ETH zurich苏黎世联邦理工学院毕业生设计：新型可塑材料装置',' ## ## ## ##作为创新材料研究的一部分，这个设计课程是用自熔焊接的方式组合塑料管，创造一个大尺度的空间家具。这个设计坐落在\r\necole spéciale d’\r\narchitecture hall建筑系馆大厅内。这个装置创造了一个功能性的室内空间地形，人们可以坐着、躺着、散步、\r\n甚至是躲藏其间。装置的材料表现出了本身所具有的机械性、功能性和美学质量，为学生们提供了一个短暂的学校空间体验。\r\n装置大部分是用手工制作，只有两块1平方米的部件是用工业机器人焊接的。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1884/eth-zurich%E8%8B%8F%E9%BB%8E%E4%B8%96%E8%81%94%E9%82%A6%E7%90%86%E5%B7%A5%E5%AD%A6%E9%99%A2%E6%AF%95%E4%B8%9A%E7%94%9F%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%EF%BC%9A%E6%96%B0%E5%9E%8B%E5%8F%AF%E5%A1%91%E6%9D%90%E6%96%99.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_1_1374258629_2a8edf3f74b3f49c688128654a840cfc.jpg@@\r\n\'straw k\' by ETH zurich graduates, zurich, switzerland##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_2_1374258629_25c40c519686f155291de96c60796f70.jpg@@\r\n椅子##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_3_1374258630_1188aaac5b8ae306739e73dda7a6e858.jpg@@\r\n整体效果##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_4_1374258630_94e8a499539d1a472f3b5dbbb85508c0.jpg@@\r\n墙面##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_5_1374258630_f28dbb56e03abb222d9897a762273d18.jpg@@\r\n细节 (从外面看)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_6_1374258630_cfaada2f1d544bf3f5e3f11b4a995af3.jpg@@\r\n细节 (从后面看)##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_7_1374258630_29571b55460384501a85fd3b64332d66.jpg@@\r\neth zurich的工业机器人实验室##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_8_1374258630_e58b7fd3a56f643bab847fe7f9d3d3f4.jpg@@\r\n机器人在制作图案##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/dbsub/375903/2013-07-19/img_9_1374258630_151f27c5dcc4bc808c493844d6351627.jpg@@\r\n带图案的部件'),(306,'AFGH architekten: rotsee湖上小屋',' ## ##\r\n每年有三周时间，在lucerne风景如画的rotsee湖面上会举办一系列湖上运动，主要以划艇为主。瑞士建筑事务所AFGH architekten\r\n设计的这座小房子漂浮在像玻璃一样平静的水面上，同时与周围美丽的自然风景和谐相称。这座三层预制木结构小屋由一个混凝土\r\n基础和楼梯间支撑，一个狭长的木船坞连接了房子和湖岸。因为建筑中将包含多种功能，所以立面被可以根据需要自由变换——\r\n就像周围的景观一样——在必要的时间转换成合适的功能。巨大的可开启遮阳板可以滑动、旋转，让建筑完全的向户外开放，同时\r\n为室内空间遮挡阳光。加工过的OSB板构成了内部墙面，而天花板和地面则选用了浅色的木板材料。自然的选材与基地相融合，雕塑\r\n般的建筑形态倒影在镜面一样的湖水上。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1885/afgh-architekten-rotsee%E6%B9%96%E4%B8%8A%E5%B0%8F%E5%B1%8B.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_01.jpg@@\r\n\'lake rotsee refuge\' by AFGH architekten, lucerne, switzerland\r\nall images courtesy of AFGH architekten##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_02.jpg@@(左) 向外开放\r\n(右) 封闭效果, 坐落湖面上##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_03.jpg@@立面效果##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_04.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_05.jpg@@\r\n入口桥梁##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_06.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_07.jpg@@\r\n入口楼梯##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_08.jpg@@可折叠的遮阳板提供了开放的视野并遮挡了阳光##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_09.jpg@@(左) 入口走廊\r\n(右) 户外观景平台##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_10.jpg@@\r\n主要观景空间##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_11.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_12.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_13.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/AFGH_lakerotsee_14.jpg@@OSB 木板 '),(307,'jean nouvel: burj doha重塑城市天际线',' ## ##jean nouvel设计的burj doha稳固的屹立在这座海湾城市的天际线上，建筑精致的、蕾丝一样的立面让人联想到这一地区常见\r\n的shanashee。这座761英尺高的建筑是一个巨大的圆柱体量，精致雕刻的网格立面是一种智能的遮阳网，非常适合多哈炎热\r\n的沙漠气候。这个设计首先实用dia-grid钢筋混凝土，包裹了整个建筑表皮，在一个巨大的尺度上创造了完全遮阳的整体立面。\r\n大厦中宽阔的绿色空间和垂直花园也是首次在卡塔尔建筑中实现。 ##这座建筑坐落在市中心的滨海路上，俯瞰着海湾水域\r\n——透过包裹着摩天大楼的圆顶帽无缝圆角可以看到无垠的蓝色海面。\r\n另外避雷装置在地面以上的海拔231.5米。burj doha是著名的哈利法塔（Burj\r\nKhalifa）的兄弟建筑，总建筑面积约110,000\r\n平方米。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##the building in context## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1883/jean-nouvel-burj-doha%E9%87%8D%E5%A1%91%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E5%A4%A9%E9%99%85%E7%BA%BF.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jean-nouvel-burj-doha-qatar-designboom00.jpg@@jean nouvel: burj doha shapes gulf city\'s skyline\r\nall images courtesy of HBS##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jean-nouvel-burj-doha-qatar-designboom01.jpg@@\r\njean nouvel: burj doha soars above qatar##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jean-nouvel-burj-doha-qatar-designboom02.jpg@@\r\njean nouvel: burj doha soars above qatar##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/jean-no