om/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom10.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom11WM.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom12WM.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom13.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom121.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom15.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/hideo-horikawa-architect-+-associates-nousfit-warehouse-designboom16.jpg@@'),(412,'mark reigelman: reading nest城市装置作品',' ## \r\n“the reading nest”是一个结合了森林和家禽的视觉视觉媒体作品。这个装置为繁忙的克利夫兰城市街道提供了一个安静隐匿\r\n的公共场所。这件作品被看成是成长、社区和知识的象征，由艺术家mark reigelman创作，他选用一种简单的2\" x 4\"木材，用\r\n200根钢索加固，覆盖了10000块板，其中有4000个没做任何处理，其它6000个涂了一层金色颜料——整个作品内部覆盖了\r\n一层金色板，外部则是两者混搭，用40000个钉子固定连接，最后成品尺寸高13\'，宽36\'。reigelman创作的城市隐居所灵感\r\n来自树下启蒙，一个历史上非常重要的象征故事。这件作品正好坐落在克利夫兰公共图书馆外面，寓意与基地相互呼应。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##\'the reading nest\' is presented by the cleveland public library and LAND studio.##[expand title=\"full article here\"  ngg_id=302]##[/expand]## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/2/view/1826/mark-reigelman-reading-nest%E5%9F%8E%E5%B8%82%E8%A3%85%E7%BD%AE%E4%BD%9C%E5%93%81.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-01.jpg@@mark reigelman builds reading nest from 10,000 palette boards\r\nall images courtesy of mark a. reigelman II##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-02.jpg@@\r\n\'the reading nest\' 位于克利夫兰公共图书馆外##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-03.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-04.jpg@@\r\nup close look at the crude construction in which 10,000 discarded palettes clad a basic wooden armature##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-05.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-06.jpg@@\r\nthe interior of the nest is covered in golden boards, the color choice drawing on the legendary griffin##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-07.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-08.jpg@@\r\ngeneral view##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-09.jpg@@\r\nthe large roost stands at 13\' tall and 36\' wide##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-10.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-11.jpg@@\r\naerial view##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/mark-reigelman-the-reading-nest-designboom-12.jpg@@'),(413,'OMA：波尔多加仑河桥梁设计',' ## ##OMA建筑事务所设计的方案在“pont jean-jacques bosc”竟赛中处于领先地位，这座桥将横跨法国波尔多的加仑河。OMA事务所\r\n将桥梁看作散步道的延伸，精心组织的小路径将承担所有过剩的交通人流。这座桥不仅仅是一条连接河两岸的通路，它还作为\r\n一个突出的静止空间，承载各式各样的活动。同时，这个设计还连接了两个完全不同的城市河岸，右岸由一系列农业景观组成，\r\n等到了左岸就变成人口更加密集的城区。最终的获胜方案将于今年12月公布，这座桥梁计划在2018年正式向公众开放。##\r\n ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1824/oma%EF%BC%9A%E6%B3%A2%E5%B0%94%E5%A4%9A%E5%8A%A0%E4%BB%91%E6%B2%B3%E6%A1%A5%E6%A2%81%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_05.jpg@@\r\n\'pont jean-jacques bosc\' by OMA, bordeaux, france\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_01.jpg@@\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_03.jpg@@\r\nlandscaping leading up to the bridge\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_04.jpg@@\r\n宽阔的步行区\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_02.jpg@@\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_06.jpg@@\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_07.jpg@@\r\n模型\r\nimage © OMA##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/OMAbordeaux_08.jpg@@\r\n模型\r\nimage © OMA'),(414,'level architects：日本ofuna住宅','level architects: house in ofuna##all images courtesy of level architects## ##这座住宅位于日本南部，当地建筑事务所采用一种纹理丰富的深色木材作为表皮材料，包裹了整个体量。水平的楼板与一个\r\n纵深的透明屋顶相交汇，这个独特的屋顶为室内带来了充足的自然光线，同时还让居住者可以观赏到周边的郊区街景。这个\r\n切割整齐的住宅建筑巧妙的消除了建筑的构造网格，在视觉上产生了一种树冠一样的效果。建筑师围绕一个开放的天井和各层\r\n楼板来布置室内外空间，将它们作为同一个空间序列，创造出嵌入式的房间体系。最终设计完成的住宅拥有流线型的室内景观。## ## ##整体效果## ## ##顶层开放空间成为街道与住宅之间的连接点， 同时为木材立面带来了变化## ##立面## ## ##顶层空间可以进行多种活动## ## ##不同位置的开窗为室内提供充足的自然光线## ## ##公共空间## ## ##顶层开放空间将室内外环境结合一体## ## ##中心天井## ## ##天井为每层空间都提供充足的光线## ## ##平静的空间氛围## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1823/level-architects%EF%BC%9A%E6%97%A5%E6%9C%ACofuna%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%85.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_001.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_002.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_003.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_004.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_005.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_006.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_007.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_008.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_009.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_010.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_011.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_012.jpg@@##http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/designboom_level-architect_House-in-Ofuna_013.jpg@@'),(415,'campos costa arquitectos：里斯本水族馆加建项目',' ## \r\n最近刚建造完工的里斯本水族馆扩建项目是由当地建筑事务所campos costa arquitectos设计的，原有的水族馆是建筑师\r\npeter chermayeff在1998年设计的，作为建筑文化遗产，位于城市中最活跃的公共广场中。在这个加建方案中，建筑师\r\n希望用合适的体量来补充原有老建筑。虽然新加建部分还是一个独立的建筑体量，但在比例上它尽量与周边已有建筑物\r\n相互应和协调。整个体量向上抬升，底部作为入口，立面上铺了5000块瓷砖，让人联想到海洋和鱼鳞，同时还提供了必要\r\n的遮阳以及视线交流和自然通风。超过1/3的面积是由交通空间组成，它们连接了新旧建筑和公共广场，同时还加设了一个\r\n临时展厅、一座报告厅和一些公共服务设施。## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ## ##全篇阅读请点击这里。','http://cn.designboom.com/cat/3/view/1822/campos-costa-arquitectos%EF%BC%9A%E9%87%8C%E6%96%AF%E6%9C%AC%E6%B0%B4%E6%97%8F%E9%A6%86%E5%8A%A0%E5%BB%BA%E9%A1%B9%E7%9B%AE.html','--- !ruby/object:Nokogiri::XML::Element {}\n','',1,2,13,'boom_cn',NULL,'\\/view\\/',NULL,'','2013-11-14','2013-11-14','http://www.designboom.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/aquarium_02.jpg@@\'lisbon aquarium extension\' by campos costa arquitectos, lisbon, p